title: denver omelet(serves 2)
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add onions, pepper and mushrooms.
In medium bowl, mix eggs and milk.
When onions become translucent, add egg mixture to skillet.
As eggs cook, shred cheese.
Add cheese immediately before serving.

title: keepin' slaw(an oldie)
directions: Shred cabbage very fine and place in bowl.
Top with 3/4 cup sugar.
Bring vinegar, salad oil, celery seed, salt, dry mustard, 2 teaspoons sugar, onion powder and turmeric to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage; cover and let stand in refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours (better overnight).
Mix, drain and serve.
Keeps crisp for a week in fridge.

title: k.f.c. biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in the 1/4 cup water; stir in buttermilk.
Add to dry mix and stir until blended.
Knead on floured board just to hold together on lightly floured surface; roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on greased cookie sheet; cover and let rise 45 minutes to 1 hour. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Line bottom of a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Whip powdered sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla for 15 minutes.

title: chow mein noodle drops
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter in large pan.
Add noodles and nuts.
Drop onto wax paper and put in cool place to set.

title: turkey stroganoff
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Add turkey and brown.
Season with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Add mushroom soup, milk and mushrooms.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Fold in the yogurt.
Serve over noodles.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Combine
all ingredients and pour into a graham cracker crust.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, sugar, flour and cinnamon. Pour into dish.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add soup.
Cut up cheese and melt (except for enough to sprinkle on top) in ground beef and add taco mix. Boil noodles and drain.
Mix all together.
Put in casserole dish and bake in oven for a few minutes at 350°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix sour cream, taco seasoning and mayonnaise.
Cover the beans and continue to layer ingredients in order listed.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Add corn, soups, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top for the last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: sandi's delight
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on the box.
Set aside to cool. Mix pudding as directed on package, adding 1/4 cup Kahlua.
Mix well.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Dust chicken breasts with seasoned flour.

Heat a large saute pan over medium heat. Add oil and saute chicken to brown. When chicken is browned on one side, turn and brown second side and add seasoning, Dijon and heavy cream. Cover and let simmer until the chicken has finished cooking.
Add a little water if sauce gets too thick. When chicken is done, remove from heat and keep warm.

title: eggnog fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Butter foil.
In a large pan, combine sugar, margarine and eggnog.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together before baking and add butter with corn flakes.
Spread on top of potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork loin with applesauce
directions: Combine flour, salt, mustard and pepper; rub over pork roast. Place flat side up in roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Combine applesauce and other ingredients.
Spread over roast. Bake 1 hour longer.
Serves 8.

title: quick pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a blender or by hand.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie plates.
The flour will make a crust.
The coconut forms a topping; the center is an egg custard filling. Delicious.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix ingredients as any other cake.
Cook at 350° until browned.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Combine soups with the vegetables; do not dilute. Top with cheese and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: quick potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown chops on one side, turn and cover with potatoes and onion.
Add white sauce.
Cover and cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender.
May use pressure cooker on medium heat for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Press ripe persimmons through colander.
Add soda to pulp. Beat in sugar.
Add milk and eggs; stir thoroughly.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
After sifted and measured, add to persimmon mixture; beat until smooth.
Melt butter; add to mixture last. Pour into greased pan that is 3 or 4 inches deep.
Bake at 300° until done.
Can be served with whipped cream.
Delicious plain. Recipe can be halved.

title: wester baked beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or cook slowly in crock-pot.

title: caramel pecan pudding
directions: Mix like cake.
Put in 4-inch deep greased pan.
Make sauce.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir in apples until moist.
Cover and cook until tender about 20 minutes; cool at room temperature and refrigerate.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening and gradually add milk.
Make into ball, wrap in plastic paper and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Divide into 16 pieces, make small ball and roll flat into 4-inch circle.
Put a tablespoon of apples in center and moisten edges and press with floured fork.
Heat about 1 1/2-inches oil and fry 2 to 3 pies at a time.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shape into ball and roll into chopped pecans. Refrigerate.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Wait until cool to slice.

title: chocolate grasshopper delight
directions: Spread crushed Oreos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Melt in double boiler the butter and chocolate.
Add eggs to cooled mixture, then add sugar.
Spread this mixture over Oreos and freeze for 25 minutes.
Soften ice cream and add 1/2 cup creme de menthe.
Pour over fudge mixture.
Crush 5 Oreos and sprinkle on top.
Freeze overnight.

title: crowd size - diet red applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Dissolve Jell-O and cinnamon in applesauce. Let cool.
Add cold water and stir.
Set in refrigerator.

title: vinegar-onion salad
directions: Peel and cut cucumbers and onions into thin slices.
Add cucumbers, onion and remaining ingredients in a bowl and toss.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim fat off roast, then freeze partially.
You want it firm enough to slice easily, but not hard.
Slice lengthwise with grain in long strips, no more than 1/4-inch thick, preferably thinner. Toss meat with soy sauce.
Arrange in single layer on wire rack placed on a baking sheet (cake racks will do).
Sprinkle with garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Turn beef over and season other side.
Bake in very low oven temperature.
Can heat oven to 150° to 175° and turn off.
After a reasonable interval, when temperature drops, again turn oven on and when desired temperature is reached, repeat procedure for about 6 to 8 hours.
Turn oven off and leave jerky in for several more hours.
Turn oven off and leave jerky in for several more hours without heat.
Store in covered container.

title: beef stroganoff - breakstone's
directions: Brown the round steak; drain.
Add onion, mushrooms and seasonings; cook 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add sour cream; stir over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Place noodles on serving platter, top with sour cream mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ann player's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add apricot nectar. Let cool, but not set. Add mandarin oranges, sliced bananas and Cool Whip. Blend well. Chill until firm.

title: lemon herb marinated chicken(yields 4 servings)
directions: In cup, mix first 5 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover; let stand at room temperature no longer than 30 minutes, turning once.
Broil 10 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, turning once. Each serving with chicken provides:
200 calories, 25 g protein, 1 g carbohydrate, 10 g total fat, 3 g polyunsaturated fat, 1 g saturated fat, 70 mg cholesterol and 330 mg sodium.

title: springtime ways with ham
directions: Set oven control at broil and/or 550°.
Diagonally slash outer edge of fat on ham at 1-inch intervals to prevent curling.
Place ham on a rack in broiler pan.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 5 minutes on each side or until light brown.
During the last 2 minutes of broiling, arrange pineapple slices on ham; brush slices with butter.

title: quick and easy no bake cookie balls
directions: Mix ingredients together except for graham cracker crumbs. Roll into small balls and roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Eat.

title: butter crescent rolls
directions: Melt oleo, sugar and salt.
Remove from heat and add milk. Cool to lukewarm and add yeast and eggs.
Add flour, mixing as you add. Mix well (dough will be sticky) and refrigerate overnight. Two or three hours before serving, roll out handful of dough in size and shape of pie crust.
Cut into wedges.
Beginning at large end, roll into crescent shape.
Let rise until double on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: eggplant tofu burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Bake on a lecithin-prepared cookie sheet for 15 minutes each side.

title: aci ezme(hot puree)
directions: Combine ingredients and serve as spread with bread, preferably fresh baked.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill for 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.

title: glazed spareribs
directions: Rub ribs with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Separate each rib and bake at 375° for an hour or until done.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Sprinkle with 1/2 sauce mix, then spoon on cottage cheese.
Top with noodles in a layer and sprinkle with remainder of sauce mix, basil, parsley and salt.
Pour tomatoes, tomato sauce and 1 cup water over top.
Bring to boil and simmer 35 minutes.
Spread cheese over top.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut shortening into flour until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Beat egg with wire whip.
Combine with vinegar and cold water.
Combine with flour, tossing lightly with fork.

title: butter noodles with spinach
directions: Prepare noodles and spinach as directed on label.
Add spinach (drained) and remaining ingredients to cooked noodles.
Cook over low heat until hot, tossing gently to coat noodles well.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk and cheese on low heat, until cheese is melted.
Combine rice, oregano and pepper in a greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Drain tomatoes.
Arrange most of the tomatoes on rice.
Add onion, lobster, tuna or crab and olives. Pour on sauce; sprinkle with potato chips.
Arrange remaining tomatoes on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook over low until onions and garlic are done.
Will keep in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler, then mix cheese, sausage and Bisquick.
Roll into about 1-inch balls.
Bake 8 to 20 minutes at 400° to 425°.
Serves approximately 50.
May be frozen before cooking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the sugar and cocoa.
Add the evaporated milk; boil for 5 minutes.
Add the butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat by hand until thickened.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Blend cream cheese and apricots until almost smooth and combine with jello.
Let set up in refrigerator. Beat slightly and fold in package of prepared Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Top with crushed nuts, black walnuts taste great!
Chill until solid.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Combine all ingredients down to spaghetti.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Put half of spaghetti in buttered baking dish.
Mix rest of the ingredients into meat and spoon half of it on spaghetti.
Top with rest of spaghetti and meat mixture in layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: praline sauce
directions: Bring water to a boil; stir in brown sugar and corn syrup. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add pecans.
Cover and chill.
Serve over ice cream.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine sugar, salt and butter.
Cook to light crack stage (285°).
Add nuts and pour on buttered cookie sheet to cool.

title: salmon loaf with cucumber sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 7 ingredients, stir in salmon.
Shape into 7 x 3 1/2-inch loaf in greased shallow baking pan; bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve with cucumber sauce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: texas hash
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat.
Add pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat through.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken-spinach picnic salad
directions: Mix soy sauce, vinegar, oil, onion, sugar and pepper and pour over chicken to marinate.
Refrigerate for at least several hours. Combine spinach, broccoli, chestnuts and bacon.
Just before serving, add chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, layer ingredients in order given. Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil vegetables together in water with bouillon.
Boil until vegetables are done.
Add the cans of soup, and cheese.
Serve warm.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Peel the onion and dice it.
Cut the celery stalk across into thin slices.
Dice the red
bell pepper.
Put the corn, onion and celery in a large bowl and add the bell pepper.
Combine thoroughly.
Put the oil, sugar and mustard powder in a medium bowl with salt and pepper.
Pour in the vinegar.
Whisk dressing ingredients together and pour over vegetable mixture.
Toss vegetables in dressing until thoroughly mixed.
Season to taste. Cover and let stand at room temperature to allow the flavors to mellow, 2 to 4 hours.
If using fresh crabmeat, pick over the crabmeat with your fingers, discarding any cartilage or shell and place in a bowl.

title: fresh tomato relish
directions: Mix together and let set in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: choc-o-nut pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and pour in pie crust.
(I always bake my pie crust for 5 minutes before adding the pie filling so the crust will be flaky.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together the jell-o, cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts. Mix well and chill.
When this has geled (set) top with the following.
Make sure the Cool Whip, cream cheese and marshmallow creme is combined together, well.

title: cheese topping for kolache
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together.
Add instant pudding according to thickness desired.
You may not have to use the whole box.

title: chili relleno
directions: Using
a
9 x 13-inch pan, layer starting with chilies, ground beef
and	then
cheeses.	Repeat.
(Reserve
1 cup of cheese mixture.)
Beat eggs, flour and milk together and pour over layers.

title: jackie's tender nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite size chunks.
Season chicken with salt, pepper and Cajun spice.
Place flour and seasoned chicken in Ziploc bag and shake well to coat.
Zip bag and set aside.
Heat empty pan on medium heat for 10 minutes.
Place oil in hot skillet and heat on medium to high heat until oil smokes. Drop in battered nuggets and brown on all sides.
Turn completely off and cover tightly to tenderize for 15 to 20 minutes, then turn burner on high crisp up outside coating (add margarine if pan is too dry).

title: brunch casserole
directions: Put bread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Mix eggs, milk and salt together, then pour over bread.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oyster chicken - the banquil, jr. way
directions: Roll
chicken
thighs
in flour.
Heat	frying	pan
on medium heat.
Put 1/4-inch of oil into pan.
When	oil
starts to bubble, put in chicken.
When all thighs
are cooked, slice them into chicken katsu pieces.
Mix oyster
sauce,
sugar and water; heat before serving.
Put sliced chicken
on
plate
or server.	Pour heated sauce over chicken.	Sprinkle
with green onions.
Drizzle leftover sauce on rice.

title: swedish meatballs and sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine ground beef, onion, bread crumbs, milk, egg, salt, allspice and pepper until blended.
Shape meat mixture into the size of large marbles using 1 teaspoon mixture each.
Arrange meatballs on one or more shallow baking pans.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes or until brown.
Remove and add to sauce.
Makes 80 meatballs.

title: twin peak crab
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
Add small amount of water to prevent drying.
Add crab meat until hot.
Put into mixing bowl and add egg, mustard, ketchup, Tabasco and seasoning to taste.
Add Mozzarella and sharp cheese.
Add cracker crumbs until consistency is right to hold mixture together.
Toast 1/2 English muffin and put on cookie sheet or pie tin.
Build crab mixture into mound on top of muffin.
Top with slice of Swiss cheese.
Toast under broiler until cheese melts.

title: frozen punch
directions: Combine sugar and water. Bring to a boil. Simmer 3 minutes. Add jello and stir until dissolved. Add juices.
Freeze in gallon milk cartons (cut bottom off to get out).
Take out of freezer about 2 hours before using.
Mash and add 1 large bottle ginger ale per gallon of punch.

title: cookie monster's famous cookie dough
directions: Put margarine into your mixing bowl.
Pour sugar over margarine.
With a fork, squash butter and sugar together until they are blended.
Crack shells of eggs and pour eggs over mixture in bowl.
Measure vanilla and pour over mixture.
With fork, blend everything in the bowl together.
Pour flour over mixture in bowl. Sprinkle baking powder and salt over mixture.
Mix everything together either with fork or your hands!
Put dough in icebox to chill (at least 1 hour).
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: homemade reese balls
directions: Melt butter. Combine all ingredients and form balls.

title: slovenian kolacki
directions: Sift flour in large bowl.
Cut in butter as for pie dough. Cut in cheese and mix until a ball is formed.
Refrigerate for 24 hours or more.
Divide dough in half.
Roll on floured surface. Cut in 3 x 3-inch pieces.
Place apricot filling in center, over lap corners.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato breakfast casserole
directions: Cover hash browns with hot water. Let stand 10 minutes. Drain well. Beat eggs and add potatoes and remaining ingredients except bacon and paprika. Pour mixture into a buttered 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with bacon and paprika. Cover dish and refrigerate overnight. Place cold pie, uncovered, in cold oven and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and eggs done. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot potato soup
directions: Saute diced bacon in large saucepan.
Add onion, celery and mushrooms.
Saute
until soft.
Blend in flour over medium heat until golden brown.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Add potatoes and
simmer
until
tender.
Season
with
salt
and pepper. Garnish with grated cheese and chives.

title: decorator's icing
directions: Sift sugar in large bowl; add other ingredients.
Beat with mixer 10 minutes (more milk may be used for thinner icing).

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until soft and translucent (8 minutes).
Add pumpkin and stock.
Stir well to mix.
Add bay leaf, sugar, curry and nutmeg.
Bring to boil, lower to simmer and cook for 30 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat.
Add cream. Return to heat.
Bring soup to hot, but do not simmer.
Serve hot.

title: mounds bars(seven layer bars)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pack really hard into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mrs. b's egg custard pie
directions: Mix the milk, eggs and sugar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until custard sets.
Grate nutmeg on top after it is baked.

title: stuffed cucumber(heritage recipe)
directions: Cut cucumber lengthwise, hollow out.
Fill with mixture, press back together, chill 2 hours, slice.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt oleo and sugar.
Stir constantly.
Bring to a boil until all oleo melts.
Pour over popped corn.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine buttermilk, oil and eggs. Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: china white decorations(inedible)
directions: In a saucepan, combine cornstarch and soda.
Gradually add water until mixture is smooth.
Heat on low, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches a moist, mashed "potato" consistency.
Turn onto a plate; cover with a damp towel.
Knead dough when cool enough to handle.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
(Dip in cornstarch and shake before using cutter.)
Make a hole with a straw or a skewer if you plan to hang it.
Lift with a narrow spatula and place on a rack to air dry at room temperature.
Can be painted when dry.

title: quick macaroons
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon 1-inch apart onto well-greased baking sheet.
Decorate with halved maraschino cherries.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove at once from baking sheet, using moistened spatula.
Makes about 5 dozen (60).

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour and 1 cup sugar.
Add milk and vanilla to flour and sugar.
In pan, heat peaches, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in dish to be used for cobbler.
Add mixture and then fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken
directions: Place chicken in rectangular baking dish.
Add onions.
Mix soup, milk and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Grate cheese over top. Refrigerate until ready to use.
When ready, place in 350° oven, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 35 to 45 minutes longer. This recipe is expandable, depending upon the size of the crowd.

title: chicken with dried beef
directions: Line bottom of glass dish with dried beef.
Season chicken breasts and wrap with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and drain juice and grease.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Add a little water, just enough to thin mixture to pour over the chicken.
Bake another hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken salad surprises
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut and mix well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in grated coconut. Makes 2 dozen.

title: mama's ripe tomato relish
directions: Cook until thick (about 1 1/2 hours) and can.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine all
fruit
in	a bowl and pour brandy over it. Leave overnight.	Combine
chilled champagne with ginger ale. Add fruit, drained.

title: texas tornado cake
directions: Pull angel food cake (bought or homemade) into pieces.
Layer in bottom of trifle bowl.
Add fresh fruit, 2 different kinds, (optional strawberry, banana, peaches, blueberry).
Mix 1 box instant pudding; layer over fruit.
Repeat if needed.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: easy stuff mushrooms
directions: Fill mushroom caps.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: peanutty macaroons
directions: Melt peanut butter over low heat.
Cool 3 to 5 minutes.
Beat egg whites, salt, sugar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Fold in coconut and melted peanut butter.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cool on wire rack.

title: sausage bundt bread
directions: Brown sausage, green pepper and onion.
Drain and set aside. Take 1 can of biscuits and with each biscuit cut into 4 quarters. Layer in bottom of Bundt pan.
Add drained sausage.
Add cheese. Layer other can of quartered biscuits.
Top with melted butter. Bake at 350° until biscuits are done, about 10 to 15 minutes. Great for breakfast!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage, then put in bottom of 9 x 12-inch glass pan.
Cut bread into cubes (without crust) and spread over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over bread cubes.
Mix well the eggs and milk.
Pour over ingredients in casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place in cold oven.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuit and beef casserole
directions: Saute beef and onions in skillet until brown.
Drain.
Combine milk, soup and cream cheese in bowl.
Add salt, catsup and beef; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Place biscuits on top; bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer or until biscuits are golden brown.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a large saucepan over heat.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Remove from heat, add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well.
Immediately drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: apple-pecan pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Freeze or pour into prepared pie shells and bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes filling for two 9-inch pies.
Keeps for 6 months frozen.

title: dakota's fried chicken salad
directions: Skin, debone and pound chicken breasts to an even thickness; dip each into flour seasoned with garlic powder, salt and pepper, then into buttermilk, then into flour mixture one more time.
Fry until golden and tender; drain on paper towels.
Slice and arrange on a bed of shredded lettuce.
Top with dressing.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Microwave butter and chocolate morsels in a 2-quart glass bowl at High 1 minute.
Mix in pecans, coconut and sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Pour filling into baked pie shell.
Microwave at Medium 8 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn at 2-minute intervals.
Stir once after 4 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding cornbread mix last.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish (greased). Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Don't overcook.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and spread on the tortillas. Roll them up like a pinwheel. Chill, slice and serve with salsa.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add marshmallow cream.
When well blended, add Cool Whip and cinnamon to taste.
Serve with chunks of cantaloupe, honeydew, pineapple, strawberries, etc.

title: fried biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, combine the powdered milk, yeast and the sugar.
In another bowl, mix the water and oil.
Add the liquids to the dry ingredients and mix well until no yeast lumps remain. Add flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring slowly.
After 5 cups are added, begin kneading in remaining flour, slowly, on a generously floured surface.
After all flour is added, continue kneading 5 minutes more.
Roll out dough in sections if necessary to 1/2-inch thick.
Keep surface floured.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter. Form scraps into a ball and re-roll and cut.
Place biscuits on a floured cookie sheet.
Let rise in a warm area for 1 hour.
Heat deep shortening to 350°.
Add biscuits without crowding.
When edges turn brown, turn once.
Biscuits cook quickly.
Remove with tongs.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with apple butter. Makes 48.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake fish, add eggs and milk and mix well.
Add crumbs and seasonings.
Form loaf.
Bake in a greased baking dish for 30 minutes at 275°.

title: whole wheat cutout cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until creamed.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Cover; chill overnight.
Roll out on lightly floured board; cut out desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes on cookie sheets lined with baking paper.

title: steak sauce(victoria sauce - rhubarb)
directions: Combine rhubarb, onion, raisins, sugar and vinegar in a saucepan.
Cook until thick, about 25 minutes.
As the mixture thickens, stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Add spices; cook 5 minutes longer.
Pour boiling hot into hot ball jars, leaving 1/8-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 10 to 15 minutes. Yield:
about 4 pints.

title: fresh peach pound cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla, then stir in flour, peaches and coconut. Cook in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°. Remove and let cool, then mix together the following glaze and drizzle over cake.

title: deer stroganoff
directions: In large skillet heat oil.
Flour meat and sauce until browned.
Add soup mix and water.
Simmer covered an hour or more, until tender.
Add mushroom soup and ketchup and heat thoroughly. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: brownie trifle dessert
directions: Mix a box of brownie mix with walnuts and bake according to directions on box.
Cool.
Break into small pieces.
Mix pudding according to directions on the box.
Use a glass trifle bowl and layer chocolate pudding, brownies and Cool Whip.
Repeat one time. sprinkle brownie crumbs on top.
May garnish each layer with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: delicious bread pudding
directions: Add cubes to hot milk and cool.
Combine sugar, eggs, margarine, raisins and spices with the bread mixture.
Pour into buttered baking dish in pan of hot water.

title: cheesy onion-dill muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl, making a well in the center of mixture. Combine milk with oil, green onions, salt and remaining 3 ingredients. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spoon batter evenly into greased muffin pans. Bake at 425° for 18 minutes. Remove from pans immediately. Yields 12 to 14.
Contains about 138 calories each.

title: moist and dark chocolate cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix together oil, hot coffee, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add liquid mixture to dry ingredients 1/3 at a time.
Mixture will be thin. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (45 to 50 minutes in Bundt pan).

title: salted peanut squares
directions: Place half of the peanuts in an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.

title: oh boy rice dish
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook rice and heat cream of mushroom soup.
Mix all together in oblong pan.
Sprinkle cheese over all of it and then sprinkle all the noodles over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni rings according to directions.
Cook drained juices from fruit with lemon juice, sugar and eggs until thick. Add pineapple and oranges.
Pour sauce over macaroni and refrigerate 12 hours.
When ready to serve, add 1 pint whipped whipping cream.
Add strawberries and bananas on top.

title: mushroom potatoes
directions: Blend soup and milk together.
Mix well and heat slowly in saucepan.
Blend in salt,
pepper
and
onion.
Then
in a greased, 1 quart casserole,
arrange
a
layer of sliced potatoes. Pour half of
the	mushroom
sauce
over
the potatoes. Then add another layer of
potatoes	and
more
of
the sauce. Sprinkle bread crumbs over the
top and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Lightly salt eggplant slices and drain in colander at least 30 minutes.
Pat dry and fry in oil until golden on both sides.

title: dirt cake
directions: Optional: Flowerpot, about 8-inches high by 8-inches diameter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion.
Add to broccoli and stir.
Pour in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Add salt and pepper.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo in pan. Add 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yum-yum cake #1
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, margarine, 3 tablespoons powdered sugar and 1/2 cup of pecans.
Pour into medium rectangular dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lean refried beans
directions: Heat oil in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until translucent, 3 minutes.
Stir in garlic, cumin and red pepper.
Cook 30 seconds.
Add beans and cook 1 minute more, mashing beans with spoon.
Stir in water; cook until water is absorbed.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into slices 1/4 inch thick.
Separate slices into rings.
Sift in ice water for at least 2 hours.
Drain, then dry. Sift flour with salt and baking soda.
Beat egg; add buttermilk and dry ingredients and beat until blended.
Dip onion rings into batter and fry in deep, hot peanut oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and mix well.
Add 3 cups flour mixed with baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add enough flour until stiff enough to roll dough.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: curried chicken and vegetables
directions: Set oven to 375°.
In a small saucepan combine first 10 ingredients.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; set aside.

title: gingerbread christmas cookies
directions: You may substitute allspice for the spices.

title: pecan breaded chicken with mustard sauce
directions: Between 2 pieces of waxed paper, flatten chicken breast with a meat pounder.
Season with pepper.
Melt 6 tablespoons butter in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Whisk in 2 tablespoons mustard. Dip each piece of chicken and heavily coat with pecans.
Place pieces in baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: french bean casserole
directions: Place all ingredients, except almonds and onion rings in casserole and dot with butter and almonds and also sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Pour onion rings over top and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and oatmeal.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Roll crescent dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan, pressing seams together.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes.
Cool.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Place crushed graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt and drizzle 1 stick of margarine over crumbs.
Mix well the lemon juice with the condensed milk and pour over crackers.
Then add 2 to 3 sliced bananas.
Cover with strawberry pie filling or one of your choice and top it off with the Cool Whip and pecans.

title: crock-pot cheese and potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, soup, milk and half the onion rings.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 9 hours (high for 4 hours).
Sprinkle remaining onion rings over top before serving.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Beat egg yolks and mix with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in melted butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Pour onto hot waffle griddle.

title: sour milk spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg and then the molasses.
Sift the dry ingredients together 3 times and add alternately with the sour milk.
Beat well.
Add the floured raisins.
Bake about 1 hr. in a loaf pan at 375°.
Ice or serve plain.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream the cream cheese.
Add butter.
Add white sugar.
Add eggs and mix together.
Sift cake flour.
Add baking powder and salt.
Mix together.
Now sift flour, baking powder and salt together, again.
Add flour mixture alternately to butter mixture with milk.
Last add vanilla or lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender in small amount of water. Season to taste. Mix all ingredients (except 5 crackers to sprinkle on top). Cook until brown at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and nuts.
Shape in rolls; wrap in waxed paper and chill. Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes. Yields 50 cookies.

title: sour cream pound cake #3
directions: Cream
margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one
at
a time, beating well after each one.
Mix soda and
salt with flour.
Add sour cream and flour alternately to margarine-sugar
mixture.
Stir
in
flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Beat eggs lightly in medium bowl, stir in corn bread mix, add corn, milk, and margarine.
Grease an 6 c. casserole dish with oil.
Place 1/2 of corn bread mixture in dish.
Add cheese, green chilies, and remaining corn mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar, creaming well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating hard after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Continue to beat, adding all flavorings.
Add marshmallows last for a real moist cake. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican supreme
directions: Brown meat; add salt and pepper.
Add soup mix; drain.
Put beans in skillet.
Heat them; mash until sticky.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with cooking spray.
Lay tortillas on bottom of pan until pan is covered.
Pour beans over tortillas.
Pour meat over beans.
Cover with 1 layer of cheese and sauce, then cover with remaining tortillas.
Put cheese and sauce on top.
Bake at 350° until very hot and cheese has melted.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Mix nuts, dates, soda, salt and butter.
Add boiling water and let stand for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs; add flavoring, sugar and flour.
Combine with date mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
(You may also divide and bake in smaller greased and floured pans.)
Take pan from oven; let sit for 5 minutes.
Cut around sides and turn out.
Wrap in foil.
When cool, put in refrigerator to chill before slicing; cut with a wet knife.
Whip cream cheese, a little milk and vanilla.
Spread on bread to make a sandwich and cut in triangles.

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, orange juice, eggs and oil in a bowl. Beat at medium speed 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and nuts. Put in 3 (9-inch) pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in water until almost tender, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Add onion, carrot, celery, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 hour and strain soup (stock).
Cut meat into bite size chunks and save for another meal.
Serve with noodles.

title: scotch mousse au chocolat
directions: Place chocolate in small, heavy saucepan.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, just until melted.
Remove from heat. Lightly beat egg yolks with 1/4 cup sugar and whiskey.
Mix in melted chocolate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, butter and salt.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add peanuts.
Stir constantly until nuts become lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in soda and spread thinly on greased platter.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Let cheese warm to room temperature.
Beat together until light, fluffy and blended.
Beat in onion and garlic.
Chill.
Roll into a ball and coat with nuts.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: freezer coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sour cream. Mix until blended. Fold in diced apples. Divide batter into two 8 x 8 greased and floured pans.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil with onion and pepper. Add olives, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and tomato soup which has been mixed with 1 can water. Pour sauce over the spaghetti. Store in refrigerator 3 days. Put into casserole and top with 1 pound grated cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350° until hot and cheese melts.

title: ranch house cookie
directions: Combine shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add both sugars to shortening, egg mixture, stirring completely.
Add flour mixture and remaining ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Roll in small balls the size of walnuts and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 100 cookies.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all together, except potato chips. Put in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Top with crumbled potato chips.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in large heavy kettle; drain.
Add all the ingredients except cabbage and macaroni.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add cabbage and macaroni; bring to boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake according to box directions.
Bake in a long, deep pan. When done, remove from oven and punch holes in cake.
Pour can of cream of coconut and milk over cake while hot. Let cool. Put in refrigerator until cold, then put Cool Whip over top, then coconut.

title: tennessee fried apples
directions: Select good cooking apples; cut crosswise into half slices. Put in hot skillet with melted butter and brown on both sides a little.
Add sugar and let cook 20 minutes longer.
Take top off to cook out some of the sugar water.
Serve hot with bacon and biscuits as a breakfast meal.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Step 1:
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
In a medium bowl, combine egg, Parmesan cheese and margarine.
Add spaghetti and toss to coat.
Put into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Press in pan to form a crust.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with stuffing mix.
Mix other ingredients; layer in
casserole dish.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sauteed liver with apples and onions
directions: Wash liver.
Place in shallow pan.
Add milk, turning slices to coat well.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Fry the bacon in large skillet. (May use margarine instead of bacon, if desired.)
Add onion and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until onions begin to brown, about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain liver well.
Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Use to coat liver well.
Wash and core apples.
Trim ends and cut each crosswise into 3 slices.
Add to skillet with onion and cook until tender and golden on each side, about 10 minutes.
In separate skillet, heat butter or margarine to cover bottom.
Add liver slices and saute until golden brown on each side, 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Serve garnished with parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican wedding rings
directions: Cream together well and chill.
Make into balls and bake at 325° until brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.

title: hobo
directions: Slice onion and place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Make hamburger patties out of ground beef and place on top of onion.
Spread sliced potatoes evenly over hamburger patties.
Add carrots on top.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook at 375° until meat is done (45 minutes or until done) and potatoes are tender.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: This makes 3 layers.
Cook at 350° until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine milk and eggs; add to flour mixture.
Mix at high speed until smooth. Stir in oil.
Bake.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes; soak overnight, using 1/4 cup salt to 1 gallon water.
Drain well; cover with boiling water to which 1/2 tablespoon alum has been added.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Drain. Cover with cold water.
Drain.
Mix spices, vinegar, sugar and water together.
Bring to a boil; add tomato slices and again, bring to a boil.
Place in hot sterile jars.
Seal.
Yields 10 pints.

title: barbecued turkey
directions: Rinse turkey and pat dry.
Melt butter and add flour to make a paste.
(Paste should be heavy enough to stick to turkey without falling off.)
Prepare grill for indirect cooking with pan under turkey.
While coals are heating, cover turkey in paste.
This prevents the need for basting.
Cook turkey on grill for 13 minutes a pound, or until it reads 170° on meat thermometer.
(Don't touch bone with thermometer.)
Add 8 coals per side every hour until turkey cooks.
This turkey is moist and beautifully pink edged with good smoky flavor.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower in salt water.
Drain.
Fry together bacon and onion.
Combine tomatoes, salt, pepper and sugar.
Put bacon, onion and tomato mixture over cauliflower.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and grated cheese on top.
Bake about 30 minutes or until light brown at 350°.

title: mint glaze for lamb
directions: Heat until jelly is melted.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
boiling water; stir in lemon juice and set
in
freezer to cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with a spoon until light and fluffy. Add cooled jello mixture; mix until smooth.
Beat milk in
a large,
chilled
mixing bowl until stiff.
Fold in cheese mixture.
Spoon
filling
into
graham cracker crusts. Chill at least 3 hours.

title: olga's wontons with crab and cheese
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sesame oil, soy sauce, and pepper until smooth.
Mix in chives and crab.
Place a wonton skin on a flat surface.
Mount 1 teaspoon filling in 1 corner.
Fold that corner over filling and roll to tuck point under.
Moisten the 2 side corners with egg and bring together, overlapping slightly. Press to seal.
Place all wontons on slightly floured baking sheet and cover while remaining wontons are made.
Can chill up to 8 hours.
Deep fry wontons in 350° oil until golden brown, 1 minute or more.
Keep in warm oven at 200° until all are cooked.
Serve with plum sauce or vinaigrette made of last 3 ingredients..

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 7-Up, and freeze.
Thaw to a slushy state and serve with half 7-Up and half slush.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and salt in microwave until melted and smooth, then stir in chips and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and spoon on wax paper until cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and clean eyes of potatoes.
Peel and clean onions, leaving about 2 inches of green stalk.
Crush potatoes.
Warm milk, seasonings and butter on low heat.
Add potatoes and simmer for 20 minutes.
Garnish with cheese.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Use leftover biscuits, break apart and lay in pie pan. Sprinkle about 1 cup sugar and chopped oleo over biscuits.
Beat eggs and mix with sweet milk and vanilla or nutmeg.
Pour over biscuits.
If biscuits absorb all the milk, add a little more. Leave a little juicy.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: three layer strawberry salad
directions: First Layer:
Place pretzels in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Melt butter and pour over.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, stirring twice. Cool.

title: syrian tomato salad
directions: Place onions and tomatoes in bowl. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serves 4.

title: cheese dipper
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat just until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: fancy fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit in order as listed. Mix Tang and dry pudding mix together. Sprinkle over fruit and toss together. Refrigerate overnight or at least for a few hours. Stir again before serving.

title: marinated tomato salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, garlic, green taco sauce, oregano, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate 6 hours or more.
Drain off oil/liquid. Sometimes you may need to add more diced cucumbers.

title: martha's torte
directions: Beat the egg whites, vanilla and vinegar until stiff.
Add the sugar, one tablespoon at a time, and beat until very stiff. Grease two 9-inch layer cake pans with oleo. Divide batter in each. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When cool, remove from pan.

title: black skillet beef with greens and red potatoes
directions: Partially freeze beef; thinly slice across grain into long strips, 1/8 inch thick.
Thoroughly coat strips with Hot 'N Spicy Seasoning.
Spray large, heavy skillet (cast-iron is good) with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat pan over high heat.
Add meat; cook, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, onion, broth and garlic.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Stir in carrots.
Lay the greens (stems removed and coarsely torn) on top and cook, covered, until carrots are tender, about 15 minutes. Serve in large serving bowl with crusty bread for dunking.
Serves 6.

title: scallion soup
directions: Place the stick of butter in a large pot.
Add scallions, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and cook slowly without browning for about 10 minutes, stirring all the while.
Remove from heat and stir in the flour.
Smooth.
Add the stock and stir over flame until the mixture oils.
Simmer for 10 minutes uncovered.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 pound of the mushrooms.
Place all in electric blender and blend.
(For easier handling, cool first.) To reheat, add 1 1/4 cups cream without boiling.
Serve garnished with raw, sliced mushrooms if desired.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet. Saute garlic and ham for 2 minutes. Add cauliflower and cook just until crisp-tender. Combine flour and cream; stir into skillet and blend well. Add salt, pepper and cayenne pepper. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 1 minute more. Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Place under a preheated broiler until lightly browned, about 2 to 4 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve immediately. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: cottage cheese delight
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: In mixing bowl, combine first eight ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with milk.
Makes about 9 servings.

title: family-size pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, stirring well.
Set aside.
Combine flour and salt in 4-quart mixing bowl.
Make well in center of flour; add yeast mixture and oil.
Stir and mix well until rough mass of dough forms.
If dough seems dry and stiff, add 1 to 2 tablespoons warm water.
Knead dough on work surface for 6 to 8 minutes, until smooth and soft.
Lightly flour large mixing bowl and dough.
Place dough in bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and kitchen towel; let rise in warm place for about 1 1/2 hours. After, punch it down; knead it lightly.
Divide in half.
Roll each piece to 13 or 14-inch circles, about 1/8-inch thick.
Place on pizza pans.
Top as desired.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Heat
oven
Drain
peaches, reserving juice. Add enough water to juice to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package except substitute juice mixture for the water.
Grease
and
flour	pans.
Pour batter into pans. Bake and cool as directed.
Cut peaches into bite size pieces. Mix
yogurt and whipped topping; fold in peaches.
Fill layers with
about half
of
peach
mixture.
Spoon
remaining peach mixture
over top of cake.
Refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken thighs until tender.
Cool and debone; save 1/2 cup of chicken broth and set aside.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer Doritos, chicken, onion, bell pepper and Velveeta cheese.
Repeat layers once or twice more.
In a saucepan, mix Ro-Tel, cream of chicken soup, 1/2 package of taco seasoning and 1/2 cup of chicken broth.
Mix well and pour over top of layers.
Use fork to make sure mixture goes through the layers.
(Poke with fork.)
Bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: bluebird betty(pet)
directions: In medium size bowl, put flour, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
Boil sugar, raisins, shortening and water for 5 minutes.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts.
Spoon into well-greased 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve in pieces on feeder tray or ground feeder.

title: all american lamburger
directions: In large bowl, combine ground lamb, tomato sauce, oats, basil, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix until all ingredients are blended.
Shape into 8 (1/2-inch thick) patties.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add juice and cranberries.
Mix well.
Chill until starting to set.
Add drained pineapple, apples and celery.
Top with chopped nuts, if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: pizza dough
directions: In first bowl, add lukewarm water and yeast.
In second bowl, put sugar, salt, shortening and boiling water, plus 1 1/2 cups of flour and mix together well.
Then add 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Add first bowl mix of water and yeast.
Mix well.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Spare dough into well oiled pan.
(Add pizza sauce and toppings.)

title: mai-kai's oriental grilled scallops
directions: Place scallops in a plastic container with lid.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over scallops.
Cover container and shake to coat scallops.
Allow to marinate in refrigerator 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cook using your favorite method.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cilantro.

title: lemon fluff salad
directions: Combine pineapple
and	sugar in a saucepan and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat. Add lemon Jell-O and water.
Chill until set.	Stir
in
pecans,
cheese
and Cool Whip and chill until firm.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together and put in 3 unbaked graham cracker crusts. Chill 1 hour.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Don't throw juice away after salad is gone; use on tossed salad.

title: impossible taco pie(the pie that does the impossible by making its own crust.)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
Spread in plate; sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater. Pour into plate.
Bake 35 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes. Serve with dairy sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
In a small pan, melt butter and add stuffing mix, tossing together.
Stir 3/4 cup of stuffing mix into vegetable mix; fill ungreased 1-quart casserole and sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Beat butter for 35 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add milk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in flour, then cherries and pecans.
Shape into 3 (7-inch) rolls.
Roll dough into coconut to coat outside.
Wrap in wax paper or clear plastic wrap; chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until edges are golden.
Makes 80.

title: squash pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well. Pour into 2 regular pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: low sodium garlic chicken
directions: In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic.
Saute 3 minutes or until chicken turns white.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon corn oil, red pepper, snow peas and green onions; saute 1 minute.
In a small bowl, stir chicken broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger until smooth.
Add chicken mixture.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend 1/2 cup oleo with 1 yellow cake mix until crumbly; sprinkle over pumpkin mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip or for different flavor, add 1/4 cup mayonnaise to Cool Whip.
This give a cream cheese-like taste.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Fry chicken in a medium-sized frying pan until cooked all the way through.
Cut each breast in half to make sure chicken is cooked thoroughly.
Cover with can of spaghetti sauce and simmer a few minutes before serving.
Top with cheese, cover and let cheese melt.
Serve with Italian bread and tossed salad.
Serves 4.

title: easy baked beans with sausage
directions: In skillet, put margarine, chopped onion and tomatoes.
Saute until tender. Add beans, cloves, bay leaves and sugar. Slice sausage in small pieces.
Cook until done (brown).
Pour bean mixture over in sausage pan.
Mix well.

title: crunch crowned brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Spread batter into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with 4 dollops of butter and sprinkle with seasoning salt. Brown pork chops in skillet, season with salt and layer over potatoes.
Pour milk over pork chops and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter.
Add corn syrup and sugar.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 1 1/2
cans of sweetened condensed milk. Mix flour with remaining 1/2 can sweetened condensed milk.
Add to sugar mixture.
Boil until hard boil, 255 degrees on a candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pour into buttered dish (15 x 10 x 2).
Let cool then cut into 1 inch squares and wrap individually.

title: orange cranberry salsa garnish
directions: Grate a small amount of orange peel into a bowl. Cut membrane away from the orange slices. Cut the slices in half and put in bowl. Squeeze the orange membrane to get juice. Add to bowl. Add the whole cranberry sauce and stir until mixed. Good with any kind of meat.

title: vinegar and oil dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Keep in bottles in refrigerator.

title: snickers cake
directions: Bake 1/2 cake mix for 20 minutes.
Melt caramels, milk and butter.
Pour over cake.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour remaining batter over cake and bake at 250° for 20 minutes and 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tandy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. While cake is still hot, spread thin layer peanut butter on top. Refrigerate until hard.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, put nuts on top, put in casserole dish; bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with crackers (Wheat Thins or shredded wheat crackers are good.)

title: parenting lab special simple sugar cookies(two-step holiday cookies are twice as fun to make!)
directions: Day 1:
Soften butter and mix with sugar until creamy.
Then add eggs.
Add other ingredients, mixing flour a little at a time. Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable frittata
directions: Adjust shelves to divide oven in thirds.
Heat oven to 450°. Grease 2 jelly roll pans and one 8-inch square baking dish.
Toss potato slices with 1 tablespoon of oil; spread in a single layer in 1 jelly roll pan.
Toss onions and bell pepper with remaining tablespoon of oil.
Spread in a single layer in other jelly roll pan.
Bake both pans 12 to 15 minutes, stirring once, until vegetables are just tender.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Sift first five ingredients into a large bowl.
Add shortening, juice and water.
Beat well.
Add eggs and lemon juice.
Beat only enough to blend.
Pour batter into two greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in medium-size saucepan.
Stir in orange peel and juice.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low; stir in butter.
Simmer for 2 minutes or until thickened and syrupy.
Add carrots.
Stir to coat and glaze. Transfer to serving dish.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 10 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: In double boiler or microwave, melt peanut butter and chips. Mix in noodles and walnuts until coated well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Chill until set.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and whip cream.
Stir in other ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Brown ground beef. Drain. Place frozen Tater Tots in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish. Mix mushroom soup and ground beef and place on top of Tater Tots. Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: snowball cake
directions: Pour water over Jell-O.
Add sugar; stir well.
Drain can of pineapple.
Add orange juice to pineapple juice to make 3/4 cup liquid
and add to Jell-O.
Refrigerate.
When partly set, beat with beater.
Take 2 cups of Cool Whip and the pineapple and add this to Jell-O.
Line a bowl with Saran Wrap.
Fill the bowl with alternate layers of cake and Cool Whip mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn upside-down and frost with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix.
Combine all ingredients well and chill until serving time.

title: almond brittle
directions: Lightly butter large cookie sheet.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat sugar, corn syrup, salt and 1/4 cup water to boiling, stirring constantly, until sugar completely dissolves. Stir in almonds.

Set candy thermometer in place and continue cooking, stirring frequently, until temperature reaches 300° or hard crack stage (when small amount of mixture is dropped into cold water, it turns hard and brittle), about 20 minutes.
As mixture begins to darken, stir constantly.
Remove saucepan from heat; stir in butter and baking soda; immediately pour onto cookie sheet.
With 2 forks, quickly pull almond mixture into rectangle about 14 x 12-inch.
Cool brittle on cookie sheet.
Break into bite size pieces.
Makes 16 servings, about 165 calories per serving.

title: june's hot beef dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until fluffy.
Add pepper, salt, chopped onions and tabasco and mix.
Chop the small jar of dried beef well, add to mixture.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Cook at 350 for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with frito scoops chips.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cook hamburger; stir in next 5 ingredients.
Place into a casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, dash of salt.
Add corn syrup and margarine.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Test with knife.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Place dried mushrooms in a small bowl.
Cover with warm water. Soak 20 minutes to soften.
Drain.
Squeeze out excess water. Discard stems.
Slice caps.

title: pistachio pudding pie
directions: Beat pudding and milk 1 to 2 minutes.
Add whipped cream. Fill in graham cracker crust.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; heat.
Mix cheese with soup; heat.
Add to green beans.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add other ingredients.
Shape with hands into 2 rolls, 2-inches in diameter, adding a little flour if necessary.
Place in wax paper in refrigerator until firm.
Can be frozen.
When ready to bake, slice thin and bake in greased pan in quick oven, 375°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Pour juices into a large perk coffeepot.
Place remaining ingredients into basket.
Place basket into coffeepot.
Upon completion of perking cycle, remove basket.
Serve hot.
Yields 30 cups.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place apples in lightly buttered deep dish baker.
Sprinkle dry cake mix and cinnamon/sugar mixture over apples.
Drizzle with melted butter.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Beat eggs.
Add pizza sauce and eggs to ground beef; stir.
Layer ingredients in order in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Dinner rolls are on top.

title: crock-pot french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender (about 20 minutes).
Put into crock-pot; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Top individual bowls with Swiss or Mozzarella cheese and broil until cheese is melted or Parmesan cheese may be sprinkled on soup before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: lemon-butter chicken
directions: Melt butter; add lemon juice to taste.
Sprinkle with oregano. Add chicken pieces and bake at 350° until chicken is crisp.
Use sauce for dipping.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and butter for 3 to 5 minutes.
Then add vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper to cool.

title: stuffed baked apples
directions: Wash baking apples and remove cores without extending hole all the way through the apples.
Stuff with mincemeat.
Place apples in open baking dish.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Rinse grated potatoes a couple of times.
Combine potatoes and onion.
Add salt, eggs and flour.
Mix together.
Add oil to a pan and ladle batter, making little pancakes.
Fry on both sides until crispy around the edges.
Makes 4 servings (about 20 pancakes).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pie shell and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poco pepper rolls
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except crescent rolls; blend well.
Separate crescent dough into 2 rectangles. Press perforations to seal.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture over each rectangle.
Starting at long edge, roll up each rectangle, jelly roll fashion.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolk and continue creaming.
Blend in flour and vanilla.
Roll out thin and cut into desired shapes.
Bake just until lightly brown, about 6 to 8 minutes.
(The secret is not to add egg whites.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix and chill in chocolate pie crust.

title: kid's candy
directions: Put confectioners sugar in bowl; add chocolate chips and milk. Add peanut butter and mix well.
Drop spoonful onto waxed paper. Chill a short time.
Eat and enjoy.

title: butterscotch refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer, on medium speed, beat butter until fluffy. Add sugar; continue beating, and add eggs and vanilla.
On low speed, add half of flour mixture until smooth.
Mix the rest by hand, forming stiff dough.
Add nuts; mix well.

title: horseradish cream
directions: Mix together and spread on each side of smoked fish (salmon and sturgeon). Roll up and serve with toothpicks. Chill until ready to serve.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Put all in bowl and mix well.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: something different with chicken
directions: Mix sour cream and seasonings.
Dip chicken in mixture.
Roll in dressing mix.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix the sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add eggs, vanilla, Pet milk and melted butter; mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 pies.

title: 3 easy meals(approximately 800 calories)
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and process until well blended.
Chill before serving for greatest taste appeal. Divide into 3 servings for a full day's menu.

title: pancakes
directions: Blend ingredients just to the point of mixed.
Cook on griddle around 400°.

title: vidalia onion pie supreme
directions: Saute onion in butter until slightly browned; spoon into pie shell.
Add milk and 1 1/4 cups of the sour cream.
Blend flour and salt with remaining 1/2 cup sour cream.

title: fat-free tortilla chips
directions: Cut tortillas into wedges.
Lay on cookie sheet.
Spray with Pam.
Salt lightly.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Store in an airtight container.
Serve with salsa or Fat-Free Guacamole Dip.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat sugar, cocoa, milk and butter, slowly bringing to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove and add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar and spread over warm pie shell.
Top with vanilla pudding mix.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.
Mixture will be crumbly.

title: egg drop and onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until they are transparent and add to boiled water.
Blend water, egg and flour and drop (by 1/4 teaspoon measure) into boiling water.
Egg Drops will float when they are cooked.
(If you would like potatoes in this soup, you can dice and cook them before adding sauteed onions.)
Serves 4.

title: one pan pork chops
directions: Wash sliced potatoes.
Brown pork chops in oil.
Add potatoes, mushroom soup and milk to get consistency of gravy.
Cover and simmer for 40 to 60 minutes or until chops are tender.
Time varies with cut of chops.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Blend in cream cheese and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and freeze. When ready to serve, thaw and cut.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix half of thawed broccoli with onion, corn, 4 tablespoons of melted butter and beaten egg.
Place bread stuffing in leftover butter. Mix with rest of broccoli and place on top of corn mixture.
Then place cheese and bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream oleo; add orange juice, powdered sugar and vanilla wafers that have been rolled into crumbs.
Add pecans and mix well.
Make into miniature balls and roll in coconut.

title: cheese garlic roll
directions: Combine all ingredients except chili powder.
Knead well.
Shape into rolls 4 inches long and 2 inches in diameter.
Roll in chili powder on waxed paper.
Refrigerate.
Slice to serve.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Combine whipped topping and condensed milk, stir into chilled pudding.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with vanilla wafers, then sliced bananas, then filling.
Repeat, ending with crushed wafers.

title: quick dip treat
directions: Dip bread into dip.
Great quick snack.

title: crock-pot baked ham
directions: Clean ham and while still damp, rub in honey.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour Coke over ham.
Turn crock-pot on high for 1 hour, then reduce heat and cook until done.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in blender for 5 minutes.
Add coconut.
Stir with a spoon.
Pour in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: south jersey tomatoes and gravy
directions: Skin tomatoes and slice; dip tomatoes in flour seasoned with salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter in fry pan over low-medium heat.
Place floured tomatoes in fry pan with butter.
Sprinkle sugar on tomatoes and cook slowly.
When tomatoes are fried, remove them and add milk and flour to fry pan to make gravy.
Stir slowly until thick.
Place tomatoes on platter and pour gravy on top.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Put rice evenly in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over rice.
Place chicken parts on top of mixture.
Dilute soup with 1 can of warm water and pour over contents in dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° until chicken is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
May uncover and bake 15 minutes longer to brown.

title: "cheese cake bars"
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts, flour and butter.
Set aside 1 cup. Pour rest in bottom of an 8-inch square pan; press firmly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: red hot lover's chili
directions: In a large skillet, cook the meat, pepper and onion until the meat is browned.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with tortilla chips and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: billionaire's pie
directions: Cook shells.
Mix ingredients; pour into shells.
Let stand overnight.
Makes 2 pies.

title: blueberry fluff
directions: Mix with blender the Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add 3 cans blueberries (in syrup), drained.
Set aside.

title: nalesniki(rolled, filled pancakes)
directions: Mix together thoroughly and fry in pan.
Roll up with filling inside.
Dip rolled pancake in egg; roll in bread crumbs and fry in butter or bacon fat.

title: spam special
directions: Cut Spam into slices.
Place slices in an oblong baking dish. Mix brown sugar, mustard and pineapple juice; pour over Spam. Bake in a 380° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with pineapple slices.

title: layer-lettuce salad
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Shred lettuce at least 1/2 dish full.
Layer each of the following:
celery, green peppers, spring onions, peas and water chestnuts.
Spread over top at least 1 cup Kraft Miracle Whip dressing, more if desired or you may use mayonnaise.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over Miracle Whip.
Use enough Cheddar cheese (shredded) to cover dish or salad.
Fry crisp, 8 to 10 strips bacon, fried crisp and crumbled.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, blend together brown sugar, granulated sugar, shortening and eggs. Add flour, baking soda and baking powder. Mix well. Add buttermilk and cherry juice, stirring well. Mix in nuts and maraschino cherries. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Sprinkle 1 side of beef steak with half of the flour mixture; pound in.
Turn beef and pound in remaining flour mixture.
Cut beef into 4 or 5 serving pieces.
Heat shortening in a 10-inch skillet until melted.
Cook beef over medium heat until brown, about 15 minutes.
Mix tomatoes (with liquid) and remaining ingredients; pour on beef.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: congealed salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Drain juice off of oranges.
Bring juice to a boil and dissolve Jell-O.
Add oranges and crushed pineapple.
Chill overnight.
Next morning, whip Cool Whip and mayonnaise to top Jell-O.
Sprinkle with the grated cheese.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a shallow casserole. Top with three slices of crumbled bread.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix together.
Let set 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: rosti
directions: Peel potatoes and onion.
Finely chop onion.
Finely shred potatoes.
Combine potatoes, onion and salt.
Heat 2 skillets. Divide butter between them.
Heat butter until slightly brown.
Add half of potato mixture to each skillet.
Cook for about 8 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Add grated cheese and firmly press mixture.
Cook, covered, for about 5 minutes until bottom is crisp. Quickly turn potato cakes over and cook on other side for 5 minutes.
You may split potato cakes in half for easier handling. Serve immediately.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Brown hamburger meat (drain).
Cook onion and bell pepper in grease from meat (drain).
In large pan, spread half of rice.
Top with half of meat.
Top this with half of onion and bell pepper. Sprinkle some of both cheeses on top of this.
Repeat steps, starting with rice.
Bake in oven at 350° just long enough for cheese to melt.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix.
Add syrup and canned milk.
Add bread, crumbled, and mix well.
Add fresh milk and vanilla.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour half into batter. Pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with raisins if desired, then sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake until center of pudding puffs, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Cook in microwave in a 1 or 2-quart casserole dish with lid for 6 1/2 or 7 minutes.
Let set for about 7 minutes.
Then they are ready to eat.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut roast into small pieces; simmer in a large pot with soup bone and suet until almost done.
Add tomatoes; cut in pieces. Chop onions and add to pot.
Dice celery, carrots and potatoes; throw in pot.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Add corn, peas, lima beans and mixed vegetables; simmer.
Add salt, pepper, red pepper seed and chili powder.
Serves a large family.

title: grandma harriett's fish stew(the easy way!)
directions: Fry enough bacon for 3 tablespoons bacon grease.
Cook potatoes and onions well covered in water until half done.
Add juice from salmon and bacon grease.
Crumble bacon into stew; salt and pepper to taste.
Add a heaping tablespoon of catsup and chunks of salmon.
Break 4 eggs onto top of stew.
Cook 15 minutes.
Believe it or not, it is delicious!
Serves 3 to 4.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushroom caps.
Place on buttered jelly roll pan. Saute chopped stems, onion and garlic in butter until onion is clear.
