Blend the cream cheese with horseradish, milk, parsley and Gruyere.
Add crumbs, onion mixture, bacon, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Spoon into mushroom caps, heaping full.
Top with shredded Gruyere and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Then broil 3 to 5 minutes, until cheese is bubbly and slightly browned.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the pumpkin pie mix, eggs and milk and pour over cake mixture.
Mix the reserved cake mix, softened butter, sugar and cinnamon and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Good with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine with powdered sugar.
Blend in vanilla, flour and pecans.
Chill.
Make ball of dough.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and place in baking dish. Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and carrot until tender in 1/2 cup water. Drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Top with 1/4 cup stuffing mix. Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: swiss cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and slowly add flour to make roux. Add milk and chicken stock, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and Swiss cheese.
Stir constantly and simmer for an additional 5 minutes. Add salt and pepper.
Just before serving, add Sauterne wine and let simmer for an additional minute.
After dishing out into soup cups, put a dash of Kirschwasser on top of each serving.
Yields approximately 2 quarts or 10 servings.

title: frozen rainbow dessert
directions: Crumble macaroons into a 9 x 13-inch pan (or large cheesecake pan with collapsible bottom).
Whip cream and pour half of it over the macaroons.
Put nuts over this mixture.
Put softened sherbet over this mixture in order listed.
Add remaining whipped cream and top with nuts, cherries or shavings of milk chocolate.
Freeze. Cut into squares when ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crisp salad
directions: Mix everything in large bowl.
Let set overnight.
May add more cheese.

title: deep south ovenly fried chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients in paper bag.
Dip chicken into milk, then place into bag.
Shake to coat well.
Place in 13 x 9-inch shallow baking dish.
Pour magarine or butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown the ground meat. Add the salt and pepper.
Add 1 small can tomato sauce.
Mix with mixer the cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream.
Add the green onions and green pepper.
In a rectangular Pyrex dish, layer the buttered spaghetti, cream cheese mixture, meat and spread 1 small can tomato sauce on top. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: any occasion punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until dissolved.
Cool.
Combine with juice and ginger ale in punch bowl.
Add ice cubes; drop sherbet in by spoonfuls.
Makes 50 servings.

title: potatoes delicious
directions: Mix
all
together
and
put
into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle
with
crushed
potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be prepared day before and refrigerated. (Omit topping until
ready
to bake.) Serves 8 to 10 persons. Recipe may be cut in half.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend milk into soup; add salt, pepper and onions.
Arrange layer of potatoes in greased casserole.
Pour in 1/2 of Cheddar sauce.
Repeat layers.
Dot with butter, cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover last 10 minutes.

title: apple nut pudding
directions: Gradually add sugar to beaten egg.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge(microwave)
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar into a large microwave dish.
Add milk, but do not stir.
Lay margarine sticks on top.
Do not stir.
Cook on High 6 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts. Mix well.
Pour onto buttered platter.
Cool in refrigerator for one hour.
Do not double recipe!

title: apple custard squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and Chex crumbs.
Remove 1 1/2 cups.
Set aside. Press remaining mixture firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine vanilla yogurt and vanilla. Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in apples.
Pour over crust. Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes.

title: handprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trace your hand or child's hand on thin paper.
Cut out.
Place flour and sugar together; mix well.
Add butter (looks like cornmeal).
Add egg and vanilla.
Turn onto floured paper, pressing into a ball.
Cut into 8 wedges.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Place pattern over and cut out handprints. Transfer dough onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake until cookies are light brown.
Cool after removing off sheet.
Decorate with icing.

title: macadamia nut cookies
directions: Cream brown and white sugar, oil and margarine.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal mix. Cut Macadamia nuts in half; stir in with chocolate chips. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until done, about 10 minutes.

title: candy cookies
directions: Cream the oil, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and combine with creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten to not more than 2 inches in diameter.
Decorate with 4 to 6 candies per cookie.
If the cookies are for a party, it's wise to make sure all cookies have the same amount of candies.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked orange roughy
directions: Arrange fish in shallow baking dish; sprinkle with parsley. Combine butter and lemon juice; sprinkle over fish.
Cover and bake 10 minutes; uncover and bake until fish flakes, about 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: buckeyes
directions: Using hands, mix butter into powdered sugar and peanut butter. Make into small balls (about 150).
Melt chocolate chips in paraffin.
Dip balls (using a toothpick) into chocolate and put on cookie sheet to dry (or on wax paper).
Leave small circle exposed for eye of buckeye.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Soak poppy seed in water; set aside.
Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs and oil.
Add poppy seed/water mixture.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.
In tea biscuit pan, bake for 20 minutes.

title: roasted root vegetables
directions: In large greased roasting pan, combine vegetables and sage. Combine oil, salt, and pepper. Drizzle over vegetables and toss.

title: pizza
directions: Chop black olives, mushrooms, green olives and pepperoni.
Use grated Cheddar cheese and shredded Mozzarella cheese.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Mix in another bowl, eggs, milk and melted butter.
Pour milk mixture over the flour mixture. Stir only enough to dampen the flour.
The batter should have lumps.
Add chocolate chips; fold in gently.
Spoon into buttered or nonstick sprayed or paper lined muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 10 large muffins or 12 medium.

title: no bake sugar-free low carb lemon cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, mix lemon jello with boiling water. Set aside. In a separate large bowl, blend cream cheese, 1/2 cup Splenda, sour cream and heavy cream. Beat until very smooth. Add jello mixture and beat again to thoroughly mix and smooth. Pour into Pyrex or Corning dish sprayed with PAM. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Whip additional 1 cup heavy cream with 1/4 cup Splenda and spread over the top of cheesecake. Top with sugar-free cherry pie filling. Serves 10. Total Carbs: 25. Carbs Per Serving: 2.5.

title: cinnamon pear pie
directions: For pie, blend together cornstarch, sugars, cinnamon, and allspice in large mixing bowl.
Add pears with any accumulated liquid.
Toss gently and pour in pie shell.
For topping, blend together ingredients and cut butter into mixture until it resembles a very course meal.
Cover pie with streusel.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix cheeses, sour cream, soup and onions.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix corn flakes and butter and sprinkle over top of potato mixture.
Bake 1 hour.

title: kelli's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.

title: chicken fajitas(low-fat)
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions, scallions and garlic in large pan with oil until opaque, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add chili powder, cumin, basil, Tabasco or hot sauce to taste (a few drops of smoke flavor may also be added).
Stir, then add chicken and stir until meat is tender and cooked.

title: potato casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes in baking dish.
Add pepper, paprika and cheese on top.
Cover with soup and cook in 400° oven using a foil cover until potatoes are done, then remove and brown for about ten minutes.
(This dish may be made the day before.)

title: crock-pot chicken wings
directions: Mix and pour over the wings in a crock-pot and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Grease pan very lightly with oil.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put one can of crescent rolls in bottom of pan going up side with rolls.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon together.
Place on top of crescent rolls.
Put other can of crescent rolls on top of filling.
Beat egg white slightly with fork.
Cover top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Mix together all ingredients except onion. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add sliced onion.

title: delicious turnip roots
directions: Simmer turnip roots in margarine until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Taste turnips.
Add sugar as needed.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Take up and sprinkle with parsley flakes (or fresh parsley).
Serve immediately.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in sherry.
Add butter.
Fold in mushrooms.
Mix soup, sour cream and all seasonings well, then fold in spaghetti. Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Fold in chicken and mushrooms; drain any juices.
Toss gently.
Put in greased 2-quart dish and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy sour pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, water and sugar to a boil. Pour over cucumbers that have been packed in jars with 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper sprinkled over them.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Brown 3 tablespoons flour in about 5 tablespoons cooking oil. Add chopped celery, onion and bell pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add okra and 1 can tomatoes and enough water to make soupy mixture. Add peeled boiled shrimp, salt and pepper.
Serve over rice.

title: skillet chicken paella
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook chicken strips, half at a time, in hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes or until no longer pink.
Remove chicken from skillet. Add onion and garlic to skillet; cook until tender but not brown. Remove skillet from heat.
Add broth, uncooked rice, oregano, paprika, salt, pepper and saffron or turmeric.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, sweet pepper and frozen peas to skillet.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Stir in cooked chicken.
Cook and stir about 1 minute more or until heated through.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: sweet and sour baked chicken
directions: Skin chicken and dry with paper towel.
In bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Shake chicken in mixture.
Heat oil slowly.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Place in baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
In small bowl, combine vinegar and sugar, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Brush chicken with sauce and pour remaining over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Blend Jell-O and pudding mixes with water and boil 10 minutes. Cool completely.
Add oranges and Cool Whip to the cooled mixture and blend.
Pour into a bowl and refrigerate.

title: cookies from a cake mix
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs and oil.
Make one inch balls. Flatten with a glass.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool one minute.
Remove from cookie sheet and transfer to cooling rack.

title: sue's pie crust
directions: Mix and press into pie plate.
Mixture will seem greasy but it is not when it is cooked.
You don't even have to roll out and make a mess!

title: nellie's favorite doggie biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, dry milk, garlic powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles cornmeal. Mix in egg and enough water to form a ball.
Pat out dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with doggie biscuit cutter and place on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.

title: zipideedooda malted
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: coconut meringue cookies
directions: Whip egg white packet with water and vanilla until stiff. Fold in dry ingredients packet and coconut.
Line cookie sheets with tin foil.
Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 - 12 minutes.
Remove cookies from foil when completely cooled.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: apple caramel dip
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients, except lemon juice, and chill.
Wash, core and slice fruit.
Dip into lemon juice to prevent browning.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cut up Velveeta (squares, cubes, whatever) in double boiler.
In large bowl, mix cocoa and powdered sugar. Add melted stuff, vanilla and nuts.
(You may have to use your hands for this.)
Pat into 2 (12 x 9-inch) buttered cake pans. Freeze.
The longer in the freezer, the better.
(You can make in November and give for Christmas.)

title: whole orange ginger cranberries
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat until the berries pop open, about 10 minutes. Cool. Refrigerate covered.

title: macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until soft mounts form.
Add 1 c. sugar and beat until peaks are stiff.
Fold in remaining sugar and all other ingredients.
Drop onto greased, floured cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix Bisquick, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Add eggs. Stir in zucchini.
Pour a small amount of batter into hot oiled saute pan.
Cook about 3 minutes on each side.
Serve while warm.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Saute the onion in the butter.
Mix the rice and warm water together and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix the Cheez Whiz, milk and soup together.
After the 10 minutes are up, place all the ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maple refrigerator cookies
directions: Make in long logs about 2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Slice and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: *Very important to use mayonnaise and not salad dressing.

title: cashew peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Press firmly on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Top evenly with marshmallows; bake 2 minutes longer or until marshmallows begin to puff.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: egg and sausage quiche
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry; flute edges.
Do not prick. Bake in 350° oven for 7 minutes.
In skillet, cook sausage; drain well.
Sprinkle hard-cooked eggs in bottom of pie shell.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine beaten eggs, cream, salt and pepper. Pour over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Stir in sour cream. Add corn syrup, vanilla, sugar, salt and butter.
Mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mountain pie
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk together.
Pour this on top of melted butter in casserole dish.
Pour fruit over top of this.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: date dainties
directions: Combine dates, margarine, sugar and egg in saucepan.
Cook for eight minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and cereal. Shape as desired.
Roll in coconut.
Let stand until cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well, then reserve 1 cup for top of cake.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: After washing and chopping cranberries, add sugar and let stand 15 minutes.
In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over orange juice to soften.
Place over low heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add gelatin mixture, celery, apple and nuts to cranberries.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours. Serve with salad dressing or whipped cream.
May be doubled for Thanksgiving dinner.

title: mother's boiled custard
directions: Lightly beat egg yolks in top of double boiler.
Gradually add milk, sugar and salt.
Cook over hot water, simmering and stirring constantly until sauce coats the spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and allow to cool.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions; let cool. Prepare chocolate mousse according to package directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces in food processor or by gently tapping the wrapped bars with a hammer.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and pepper flakes.
Spread in bottom of quiche baking dish. Spread pizza sauce on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle on pepperoni, green onion and green peppers. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: sparkling strawberry punch
directions: In covered blender container at high speed, blend strawberries and undiluted lemonade concentrate until they are thoroughly blended.
Pour strawberry mixture into a chilled large punch bowl. Add wine and remaining ingredients except orange slices.
Stir punch until sugar is completely dissolved.
To serve, garnish punch with orange slices.

title: pecan chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add one cup at a time. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 8 dozen large cookies.

title: gertrude's coke cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and Coke together until blended.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Prepare crust, brush with olive oil.
Pour can of tomato sauce over crust.
Spread garlic and seasonings over sauce and crust. Top with cheese.
Put vegetables over cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grandma davis boiled custard
directions: Sift sugar, cornstarch, and salt 3 times.
Mix with other ingredients and cook slowly until mixture thickens.
Pour into custard cups and chill.

title: gershwin's goulash
directions: Cook beef in oil in Dutch oven until brown.
Add the next 10 ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour.
Stir in kidney beans and pickles.
Cook for 30 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf.
Add 1 teaspoon salt to boiling water.
Add macaroni gradually to water. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Drain in colander.
Combine with goulash; heat through.
Yields 10 servings.

title: vegetable garden dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: buckeyes
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler. Pick up balls with toothpick.
Dip into chocolate.
Lay on waxed paper.

title: christmas fragrance(christmas tidbits)
directions: Simmer in open pan on stove. Makes a special holiday fragrance.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients. Chill, if desired.
Use tablespoon of dough for each.
Shape into balls; place about an inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make indention in the center of each ball and put 2 or 3 semi-sweet pieces in each indention.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: calzone
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 12-inch pizza pan with foil and spray with nonstick spray coating or grease with shortening. Press dough onto foil in pan, forming a 10-inch circle.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in hot oil. Add garlic; simmer. Add soy sauce, salt, and water; cook 45 minutes. Add vegetables. Cook for 10 minutes. Blend 1 c. water and cornstarch; add and stir. Add tomatoes; cook 5 minutes. Serve over rice. 4 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thaw shrimp according to package.
Add all ingredients, except shrimp, until well combined.
Stir in shrimp.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: creamy nuts
directions: Combine sugars and cream in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugars are dissolved.
Continue to cook over low heat until mixture reaches 246° or until drop of mixture in water forms firm ball.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts. Stir until light sugar coating begins to form on nuts.
Move onto wax paper and separate nuts.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter, milk and cocoa 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until peanut butter dissolves.
Add oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
When cool, remove from paper.

title: cracker bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Gradually stir in flour one cup at a time, using enough to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth (5 minutes).
Divide into 4 equal portions and shape into balls.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll each ball into a 12-inch circle.
Place on greased cookie sheets. Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle with salt.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned in 400° oven.
Cool completely on wire rack.
To serve, break into pieces.

title: butter dips(bread)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in oven in oblong 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Remove pan when butter is melted. Sift dry ingredients together, then add milk.
Stir slowly with fork until dough just clings together.
Turn onto well floured board.
Roll over to coat with flour.
Knead lightly about 10 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness into 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
With floured knife, cut dough in half lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 16 strips.
Pick up cut strips in both hands and dip each strip in melted butter.
Next, lay them close together in the same pan in which butter was melted.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown. Serve hot.
Makes 32 sticks.

title: mocha tart
directions: Mix cold strong coffee in with butter until you get a good mocha color, then work sugar, egg yolks and nuts into mixture. Into a deep Pyrex loaf pan, line the sides and bottom with the ladyfingers.
Layer the ingredients in this way:
egg mixture, ladyfingers, egg mixture and ladyfingers.
The top layer should be ladyfingers.
Fill to the top of the loaf pan.
Freeze overnight. To serve, slice the loaf with a sharp knife.
Serves 12 people.

title: honey jumbos
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Roll (not too thin). Cut with doughnut cutter or oblong sizes.
Bake at 350° to 400°.
Cool. Frost with powdered sugar frosting, if desired.

title: no mix cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread it evenly over bottom of pan.
Spread remaining ingredients (except milk) evenly in pan, then drizzle condensed milk over mixture.
Bake on 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: panned oysters
directions: Cream butter with lemon juice; spread on toast.
Quarter each slice.
Place an oyster on each quarter; sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Place on a baking sheet and bake 5 to 6 minutes or just long enough to plump oysters.
Makes 24 pieces.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, onions and seasonings.
Form into small balls. Cook in hot oil in skillet, turning frequently, until light brown, but not crusty, on all sides.
Add Hunt's tomato sauce and water.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in long pan.
Add fruit.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk; pour over fruit.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with jello.
Add pineapple, then add Cool Whip.
Mold.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken almond spread
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with all the salts, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, parsley and sour cream.
Stir in almonds, chicken and mushrooms, all finely chopped.
Mold in serving dish; refrigerate until chilled.
Unmold.
Spread and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with Melba toast rounds or crackers.

title: basic vanilla ice cream
directions: Stir cream, sugar and vanilla to dissolve.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Place in a Corning Ware baking dish.
Drain and rinse sauerkraut; spread over chicken.
Cover this with Thousand Island dressing; place Swiss cheese over all. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool slightly to let juices set.
Enjoy!!!
Yields 4 servings.

title: grandmother's raised rolls(never fail and easy)
directions: Combine shortening and boiling water, letting it melt while cutting it up.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to shortening mixture when it has cooled down to warm.
Add remaining ingredients and knead for 5 minutes, using enough flour so it will no longer be sticky.
Roll out and cut into 20 to 24 dinner rolls or spread with butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up and cut off 3/4-inch pieces to make 16 to 20 cinnamon rolls.

title: teriyaki shish kebabs
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; toss with beef.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Drain beef, reserving marinade.
Thread meat, pineapple and vegetables alternately on long skewers.
Grill over hot coals for 15 to 20 minutes, turning often, or until meat reaches desired doneness and vegetables are tender.
Simmer the marinade in a small saucepan over low heat for 15 minutes.
Remove meat and vegetables from skewers.
Serve with marinade.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Rinse and drain; combine with butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Brown beef with onion; drain.
Spoon on top of spaghetti noodles.
Pour spaghetti sauce over all and sprinkle liberally with Mozzarella cheese.
Arrange slices of pepperoni over surface.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Let it bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil; continue baking 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into pieces.

title: chili egg puff
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until light (yellow color).
Add all ingredients, except chiles.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in chiles.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until top is brown and center will be firm. Spoon picante sauce on top.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: In food processor, grind cranberries into small pieces.
Put in large bowl with sugar. Cut orange into small pieces (peeling and sections). Grind in food processor until completely ground. Put in bowl with cranberries and sugar.
Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add cold water.
Chill until partially set. Add jello, celery and nuts to cranberry-orange mixture.
Pour into 3-quart Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: pecan pumpkin pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Top with chopped pecans. Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Chill; served topped with whipped cream.

title: rita's easy tortillas
directions: Mix flour, Bisquick and warm milk in bowl.
Knead until smooth.
Divide into 1-inch balls.
Let set, covered, 5 minutes to 2 hours.
Roll each ball out on floured board to form a circle. Roll quite thin.
Brown in greased frying pan or griddle.
Serve warm or use to make burritos.
Makes 8 medium or 16 small.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Mix sugar, water, egg whites, corn syrup and salt in top of double boiler.
Beat about 1 minute until blended thoroughly. Place over boiling water.
Beat constantly with electric mixer on high speed until frosting stands in peaks, about seven minutes, scraping sides occasionally with rubber scraper.

title: banana-gelatin dessert
directions: Combine the two gelatins, hot water and soda together in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until almost gelled. Add bananas, pineapple (reserve juice) and marshmallows to the gelatin. Refrigerate until completely set. Add water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup. Then combine sugar, cornstarch and eggs with the juice. Cook until thickened. Let cool. Fold the Cool Whip and cream cheese into the cooled mixture until smooth. Spread over gelatin.

title: super shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Pour into glasses and serve.
Serves two.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound breasts until thin.
Dip in egg, then coat with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Pour butter and olive oil into pan with garlic and heat.
Saute chicken until golden brown on both sides.
Add wine, juice of 1 lemon, mushrooms and basil.
I like to serve with pasta, garlic bread and tossed salad.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In a 3-quart heavy saucepan, melt margarine and butterscotch morsels. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Add next 6 ingredients to mixture in saucepan, stirring well.
Fold remaining ingredients into saucepan.
Spread into pregreased pan. Bake for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
(Batter will still be jiggly.)
Cool and then cut into squares.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add strawberries to water and sugar.
Cook until thick and clear.
Stir in 2 to 3 drops food coloring.
Stir in rest of strawberries (don't add water) into pie crust.
Chill 3 hours and top with whipped cream.

title: red snapper
directions: Brush a very thin layer of mayonnaise on both sides of red snapper.
Combine equal parts (1/2 cup or more) of Parmesan cheese, sesame seed and wheat germ and stir.
Coat fish with combination.
Place fish in greased glass baking dish.
Cook at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter and oil in pan, then add marshmallows.
Stir until creamy.
Take off stove and set aside.
Mix popcorn, nuts and M&M's in a large bowl.
Then pour marshmallow mix over it.
Mix well.
Press into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Let cool 1 hour, then remove.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs slightly in large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar and vanilla.
Cut up zucchini and put in blender.
Blend thoroughly; do not drain.
Add to mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Stir into egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Open out chicken breasts, boned side up and flatten with wooden mallet until not quite 1/4-inch thick.
Salt and pepper breasts.
Cover half of breast with thin slice of ham and slice of Swiss cheese.
Tucking in the sides, roll the breasts as for jelly roll.
Press to seal well.
Dust chicken with flour, dip in egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Cover and chill thoroughly, at least an hour.
Fix ahead and refrigerate overnight.
About an hour before serving time, fry rolls in deep hot fat (375°) for 5 minutes or until crisp and golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Place rolls in shallow baking dish and bake in slow oven (325°) for about 45 minutes.
Serve on warm platter.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: honey blueberry bread
directions: Pour milk over cereal. Let stand until cool. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries. Add sugar, egg, shortening and honey to cereal mixture. Then add flour mixture, stirring only enough to dampen flour. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Wrap in wax paper. Store overnight before slicing. Makes 1 (8 x 4) loaf.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Brown beef and onions; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread into pie plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together and press in bottom and side of a 10 inch spring pan.
Set aside.

title: ginger-molasses cake
directions: Cream molasses, sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add boiling water with soda last.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until done.

title: puffy eggs in casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: *You can substitute breakfast sausage, browned and cut into pieces, instead of bacon.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown the hamburger and drain well.
Mix with the refried beans and taco sauce.
Set this aside, then shred the cheese and dice the onion.
In separate bowl, mix cheese and onion together.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 2-quart glass measure, combine sugar and corn syrup. Stir. Cook at High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir well. Cook at High for an additional 3 1/2 minutes. Add butter and vanilla, stirring well.
Cook at High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently until light and foamy.
Immediately pour mixture onto buttered cookie sheet. Spread thinly. Cool.
Break into small pieces.

title: hidden valley ranch chicken
directions: Dip washed and dried chicken in melted butter.
Dredge in bowl of dressing mix, Parmesan cheese, and crumbs.
Bake uncovered in well-greased baking dish at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: connie's casserole
directions: Cook rigoletti according to package directions and drain.
Set aside.
Fry onion and pepper in large pan with chicken.

Add hamburger or ground turkey. Fry until cooked, but not dry. Add salt, tomatoes, cheese, bay leaf, oregano, marjoram and drained rigoletti. When cheese has melted, put into a greased casserole dish. Top with 4 slices of cheese.
Melt cheese under broiler.

title: girl scout cookie drink
directions: Make hot chocolate according to directions.
Add shot of peppermint Schnapps and stir.
Garnish with mint leaves (seasonal) and whipped cream.
Makes 1 cup.

title: vidalia onion and spinach salad
directions: Pour your favorite dressing over salad and toss.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into 2 crusts. Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Makes 12 generous servings.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Mix ingredients well by hand.
Pour into a 9-inch deep dish crust.
Bake slowly at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole (2)
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli until slightly tender.
Brown onions with margarine.
Melt cheese with soup and milk.
Mix together then put in casserole dish.
Put cracker crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil boneless chicken until thoroughly cooked.
Then cut it up and place in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Combine the sour cream and soup in a separate bowl.
Pour this on top of the chicken.
Then pour the poppy seed over this.
Crush the Ritz crackers and pour over top.
Then melt the stick of margarine and pour over the crackers.
The crackers should cover all of the mixture.
Bake at 375° until cracker crumbs are golden brown.

title: mexican rice
directions: The rice should be washed until the water is clear.
Let it drain.
Heat oil and cook the rice for about 15 minutes.
Add onion with salt and pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Next, add tomato sauce.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes, then add water and chicken bouillon.
Dissolve the chicken bouillon completely.
Cook until water is absorbed, then add green peppers to top of rice and cover it with aluminum.
Cook for 5 to 10 more minutes, until rice is tender.

title: cool and creamy chocolate pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended. Gradually add syrup until smooth.
In other bowl beat whipping cream until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into crust; cover.
Freeze until firm.
Before serving (optional) garnish with shaved candy bar or fresh fruit.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add butter and milk.
Bring to a slow boil, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking until mixture reaches desired thickness.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in lemon juice, honey and lemon peel.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hot seafood casserole
directions: Mix crab and shrimp; set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
In a large bowl, fold in seafood.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch square casserole. Toss bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Great over rice.

title: squash casserole #1
directions: In mixing bowl, combine squash, soup, sour cream, onion, carrot, salt and pepper and a dash of red pepper, if desired. In buttered casserole dish, sprinkle a layer of bread crumbs and then add squash mixture. Cover with another layer of bread crumbs and dot butter or margarine on top.
(Or squeeze liquid margarine over top.)
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin fritters
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, flour, salt and spices together well.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add baking powder.
Fry in hot oleo until brown.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top before serving. If pumpkin is wet, 2 cups of flour may be needed.

title: walnut-cheese spinach salad
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring raspberries and sugar to a boil.
Cook for 1 minute.
Strain and discard pulp.
In a blender, combine the raspberry juice, oil, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce; cover and process until smooth.
In a salad bowl, combine the spinach, onion, cheese and walnuts.
Drizzle with desired amount of dressing; toss to coat. Refrigerate any remaining dressing.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done (boil).
Pull meat off bone in bite size pieces.
Combine chicken, sour cream, salt, pepper, garlic salt and cream of chicken soup.
Put in greased baking sheet.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with one stick melted butter.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well; refrigerate overnight or all day.
Shape in small 1-inch balls.
Can be frozen.
When ready to use, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french bread pizza
directions: Cut loaf of bread lengthwise and then cut in half.
Spread with pizza sauce.
Add oregano; add mushrooms, meat, then cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until cheese has melted.

title: chops and kraut
directions: Layer in crock-pot a little sauerkraut, onion and pork chops. Layer again until all is gone.
Cook on low heat 6 to 8 hours. Serve with applesauce.

title: chocolate almond sodas
directions: Break chocolate bar into small pieces.
Place in blender container with instant coffee, almond extract and water.
Blend on medium until smooth; add milk and blend.
Place one scoop ice cream in each of 4 soda glasses.
Pour chocolate mixture equally into glasses.
Fill with club soda.
Serve with long handled spoons and straws.

title: shrimp and green noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Line a greased casserole with noodles.

title: microwave chicken marengo(4 servings)
directions: Combine bread crumbs and spaghetti sauce mix in plastic bag. Shake chicken pieces in bag until coated.
Place chicken, skin side up, in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with any remaining crumb mixture.
Cover with waxed paper.

title: chicken dirty rice
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven. Add onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic and flour. Cook over medium heat until flour is a deep red-brown. Stir constantly to prevent burning. Stir in ground chicken, giblets, salt, black pepper and red pepper. Cook until meat is brown. Blend in broth. Cover and simmer 25 minutes. Stir in cooked rice and onion tops. Cook another 5 minutes longer. Serve hot. Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole(97% fat-free)
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; cool.
Cut into small pieces and place in buttered oblong casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream; pour over chicken.

title: cheese and shrimp wedges
directions: Mix meat, cheese, margarine and mayonnaise with electric mixer; mix well.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze for approximately 1 hour and cut into wedges.
Store in freezer in a freezer bag. Before serving, broil until golden copper, about 5 minutes, but watch them carefully.

title: punch
directions: Chill well and serve over crushed ice.
Garnish with mint or orange slice.

title: milk duds cookies
directions: Beat margarine, peanut butter and sugars together until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt to margarine mixture.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Press Milk Dud into the center of ball and roll dough around it.
Roll each ball in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Do not use cookie sheet that has a nonstick surface. Bake at 350° until cookies start to crack on top, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 20 cookies.

title: cinnamon roasted sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In small bowl, whisk together honey and oil.
Rub each sweet potato halve with honey and oil mixture.
Season potatoes with salt and pepper.
Press a cinnamon stick between matching halves of each sweet potato and wrap potatoes in foil.
Place on a baking sheet and roast for 30 min. Remove foil from potatoes and arrange skin side up on baking sheet.
Place cinnamon sticks next to potatoes and return to oven. Bake until potatoes and cinnamon sticks brown lightly; about 30 min.
Transfer to serving platter.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except raisins and cinnamon.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Last 1/2 hour, add raisins.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thinly.
Use a food processor, if available.
Lightly grease an ovenproof baking pan (13 x 9-inch). Layer potato slices in pan, sprinkling each layer with salt, pepper, nutmeg and cheese.
Press garlic over mixture.
Add cream and milk.
(You may prepare ahead of time up to this step).
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until potatoes are soft and creamy and golden brown on surface.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large, heavy pan mix ground chuck in hot oil.
Saute onion and garlic until brown.
Add tomato paste and sugar.
Fry for a few more minutes and add water and other ingredients, except Parmesan cheese and lasagna noodles.
In separate pan, cook lasagna noodles in hot salted water; when done remove from fire, drain and rinse until cooled.
Add 1 layer noodles and layer of sauce.
Continue until all is used.
Add the cheese to top.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients for about 4 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden.

title: cow chip cookies
directions: Melt together oleo and Crisco and blend in the sugars; add four eggs and mix well.
Then mix in all other ingredients.
Use 1/4 c. batter per cookie.
Batter can be flattened slightly to make cookies thinner.
If you do not flatten batter it will make the cookies thicker.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat; gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.

title: mini pecan pies
directions: Let cream cheese and butter soften to room temperature.
Blend cream cheese and butter well; add flour.
Chill.
This makes dough easier to work with.
Use miniature muffin pans.
Pinch off marble size balls and shape in muffin pans.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Pour milk into dry ingredients, then add melted butter.
Blend thoroughly and pour into a shallow baking dish.
Place peaches on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 40 minutes. Serves six.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients and spread with mayonnaise. Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Set overnight and toss to serve.

title: apple raisin sauce(pancake topping)
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups cider, brown sugar, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir over low heat.
Mix 1/4 cup cider, brandy and flour separately.
Then stir into warm mixture.
Stir until it begins to bubble. Then add apples and cook until tender.
Serve over pancakes.
Serves 6.

title: laura's peanut butter pie
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter; add brown sugar and graham crackers. Press into 9-inch springform pan. Put in refrigerator to cool. Whip presoftened cream cheese with beater. Add peanut butter, sugar and 2 tablespoons melted butter. Whip to smooth consistency. Whip cream and vanilla in a separate bowl. After cream forms stiff peaks, add to peanut butter mixture by hand. Mix until smooth. Pile into pie shell.
Chill 6 hours. About an hour before serving, melt chocolate with coffee in double boiler until smooth. Spread over chilled pie. Chill until chocolate is set.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, carrots, salt, pepper and cheese. Cover with celery soup, mixed with 1 can milk.
Cover potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or microwave until veggies are tender.

title: overnight cinnamon buns
directions: Grease Bundt pan or round Corning Ware pan.
Drop frozen dough into a bag of cinnamon.
Make sure all dough balls are covered with cinnamon.

title: marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and place meat in for several hours or overnight.
Turn meat occasionally.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Put in crock-pot and cook on low for 5 hours.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Stew chicken and debone, reserving broth.
Cook noodles in broth to which soup has been added (undiluted), according to directions on package.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and margarine; blend at low speed until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press 2 3/4 cups of crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
To remaining mixture, add cinnamon, baking soda, salt, sour cream, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon evenly over base.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
If desired, serve with whipped cream or ice cream and toppings. Makes 12 servings.

title: kielbasa with noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package; drain.
In skillet over medium heat, cook kielbasa and onion until brown, stirring often. Spoon off fat.
Add soup, milk, beans and pepper; heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover 5 minutes stirring occasionally.
Stir cooked noodles into skillet.
Heat 2 minutes or until noodles are hot.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue chicken crock-pot style
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Cover and cook on low about 7 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Use
1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup granulated for lighter recipe (less sweet).

title: chicken-pineapple casserole
directions: Combine all but noodles.
Fold in 1 cup noodles.
Put in dish. Sprinkle rest of noodles on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cover the bottom of dish with refried beans.
Now start layering lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, olives, sour cream, onions, peppers and taco sauce.
Repeat with what's left.
Ready to serve with taco chips.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Form into balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: slow cooker cider
directions: Place cinnamon, cloves, and allspice in a double thickness of cheesecloth; bring up the corners of cloth and tie with a string to form a bag.
Place cider and brown sugar in a slow cooker; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add spice bag.
Place orange slices on top.
Cover and cook for 2-5 hours.
Remove spice bag before serving. Yield: 2 quarts.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Put peppers (discard seeds) and onions through chopper.
Add salt and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain liquid and discard.
Add vinegar and sugar to vegetables.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars.
Adjust lids at once.
Process in boiling water bath (212°) for 5 minutes. Remove jars from canner and complete seals unless closures are self-sealing type.
Makes 6 pints.

title: fried apple pie
directions: Mix flour and shortening.
Add water until moist.
Pour onto floured surface.
Roll out small pieces into rounds.
Put cooked cold apples on bottom half; fold over and press edges with fork. Fry in skillet with 3 to 4 tablespoons Crisco on medium-low heat. Frost with powdered sugar and milk glaze.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Pour in remaining batter and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: granny's zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into 2 large or 4 small bread pans that are well-greased.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: caramel chocolate
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt Kraft caramels with Milnot.
Mix cake mix with melted butter, milk and pecans.
Spread 1/2 cake mixture in a greased and floured pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Take out of oven and pour semi-sweet chocolate chips on this. Spread the caramel mixture on, then the rest of the cake mixture on top.
Bake 13 minutes, then let set several hours.

title: rich cookies(vanilla wafers)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, then eggs, flour and vanilla.
Arrange by teaspoonfuls on lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Spread thin with knife dipped in cold water.
Put on top raisins or nuts, if desired.
Makes 60.

title: applesauce carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and spices in large mixer bowl.
Add applesauce and butter; beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl and beaters occasionally.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost with Cherry Apple Frosting.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine the crushed wafers, walnuts, 1 cup powdered sugar, bourbon, cocoa and corn syrup in a medium size bowl.
Dust hands with powdered sugar and roll the mixture into small balls.
Roll each ball in powdered sugar.
Store in a cool place until ready to serve.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Sift flour.
Measure and sift again with salt.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Add pecans. Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten cookies and bake in a 325° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add rhubarb.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust; dot with butter. Cover with other pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine milk, oil and eggs.
Beat to mix.
Add dry ingredients and stir well.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warmed buttermilk.
Mix the flour, salt, soda and sugar together.
Add the buttermilk and shortening to the flour mixture.
Roll out in white flour.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour at room temperature.
Roll out again and cut into biscuits.
Let rise 10 minutes, then bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin dip with gingersnaps
directions: Combine sugar and cream cheese.
Blend/beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
(Makes a large bowl; can be cut in half.)

title: brisket of beef with hunters sauce
directions: Place brisket in 2 layers of heavy-duty foil.
Sprinkle 1/2 package soup mix over meat.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Seal tightly. Bake 4 hours at 300°.
Refrigerate meat and juices separately.

title: cherry salad(a dean family recipe)
directions: *Can substitute Carnation evaporated milk, diluted with a little milk.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Combine sugar, yeast, salt and 1 cup flour in a large bowl. Heat water and butter to 128° to 130° with candy thermometer.
Add and slowly beat on low into flour mixture for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1 more cup of flour.
Again, beat slowly to mix, then medium speed for 2 minutes.
Take beaters out and add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead.
Watch you don't get too much flour in them. When dough doesn't stick to board, put into greased bowl and let rise to double in bulk.
Punch down.
Divide in 4 parts.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Using pastry brush, spread with melted butter. Cut in pie shaped angles and roll like you would for crescent rolls.
Start at wide area first.
Let rise.
Partially bake at 400° until begins to brown.
Cool.
Freeze on cookie sheet, then bag them.
When you want rolls, take out desired amount and finish baking them.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter in microwave or over double boiler.
Add Rice Krispies and salted peanuts.
Mix up and spread on wax paper on sheet cake pan.
Chill in refrigerator and break apart.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine butter and flour in large saucepan; place over low heat. Gradually add milk and chicken broth, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened. Stir in chicken, pepper, salt and vegetables. Mix well. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Roll pastry out to fit dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy lasagna recipe
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain grease.
Pour spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Boil noodles as directed; drain.
In a large casserole dish, layer ingredients as follows:
noodles, meat sauce and both cheeses.
Repeat until all is used.
Put extra cheese on top.
Place in 350° oven until cheese is melted on top.

title: make ahead fruit salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Mix well until blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients and chill.
You can make this salad hours ahead.
It tastes even better when the fruit flavors mingle longer with the soft little marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: danish raspberry bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, oats and sugars (not confectioners sugar).
Add melted butter and stir to blend.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Season to taste.
Combine these ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish
Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni slices.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: bacalao salad
directions: Boil codfish and rinse to take out extra salt.
Slice onion and the peppers in rings.
Cook beans.
Slice the eggs in rings.
Take a platter; place the boiled potatoes, cut in rings or rounds on bottom.
Add flaked bacolao (codfish), add French-cut green beans. Add the colored peppers and onions.
Place rings of eggs on top. Pour olive oil and vinegar over all of it.

title: avocado sherry bisque
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Saute onion until soft. Stir in flour.
Add chicken stock and cook until thick.
Stir in lemon juice, sherry, garlic, salt and pepper and simmer for 15 minutes.
Blend diced avocados with half and half until smooth. Add to saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes.
Chill and serve garnished with chopped parsley.
Or serve hot.

title: date nut balls
directions: Measure margarine, dates, cherries and sugar into medium size saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes a soft paste.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Measure by level tablespoonful onto waxed paper or buttered baking sheet.
Shape into balls.
Let stand until cool.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.
Good for Christmas candy.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with a little milk to a soft dip stage, then add chopped shrimp, onions, salt and pepper.
Mix very thoroughly.
Serve with crackers or Fritos.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Cook 10 minutes longer with the other stuff.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chocolate dot pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs, then add pumpkin, oil and bran cereal.
Add dry ingredients, mixing only until combined.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: corn pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Press into greased, glass baking dish.
Cook onion and pepper in remaining butter.
Blend in flour; add corn.
Cook until thick.
Pour into crust.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix eggs, evaporated milk, pumpkin, sugar and seasonings together.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, lightly greased and lined with wax paper.
Sprinkle cake mix on top; distribute lightly with fork so as not to mix in.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Press in.
Drizzle top with melted butter.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Use toothpick to check for doneness.
Cool thoroughly; loosen sides and turn upside down to peel off paper.
Cut into 1-inch squares and garnish with whipped cream.
Makes 117 one-inch pieces.

title: punch bowl cake (trifle)
directions: Tear cake into pieces and place in a large bowl.
Spread pudding over the torn cake.
Layer pineapple, pie filling and Cool Whip.
Garnish as desired.
Cover and refrigerate until served.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 340°.
Mix milk, egg and flour in a large mixing bowl.
Stir good.
In baking pan, pour blueberries.
After dropping the mixture on the blueberries, pour on melted butter over crust and blueberries.
Then dobb sugar over crust.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Blend all ingredients until mixed. Pour into 13x9 cake pan. Chill at least 1 hr. Cut in squares and serve.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients with hands (it will seem dry at first but keep kneading).
When well mixed, it will be a real thick dough.
Roll into small balls (they will rise some when cooked).
Can be frozen and cooked as needed.
Cook at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: jello dessert
directions: Put pretzels on bottom of 8 x 8 pan and pour butter over them. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix Cool Whip and cream cheese and refrigerate.
Prepare jello, using 3 cups water instead of 4, and add the fruit.
Let set up a little.
Once the pretzels have cooled, spread the cream cheese mixture on top.
Be sure the edges are sealed so jello can't leak through.
Then pour jello on top of cream cheese mixture and refrigerate until set up, then serve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool until partially set.
Stir in apples and nuts.

title: golden nuggets
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender with dash of salt.
Do not overcook.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients, mix well and pour over hot carrots.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Will keep a week or more in refrigerator.

title: mom's red beans and sausage
directions: Sort and wash beans and then rewash to make sure they are clean. Fill pot with water and boil. While beans are boiling, fry sausage, onions, bell peppers, onion tops and parsley together until tender or just brown around the edges. Once this is done and your beans are starting to split open, combine everything together in the pot. Now add the bay leaf and the garlic. As you stir the beans, smash the beans on the side of the pot for creamy ones. Cook until sauce is thick and beans are tender. Remove bay leaf before you serve.

title: no name cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add the rest; blend well. Bake at 350° on greased and floured 10 x 15-inch sheet cake pan for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry orange bread
directions: In large bowl, mix well all ingredients except blueberries and nuts until mixture is moistened.
(Do not overbeat.) Gently stir in blueberries and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake 50 minutes at 375° or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: quick fruit crunch
directions: Empty pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cake mix.
Pour melted butter on top of everything.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples and coconut.
Add apples and pour into a 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl, mix until creamy, smooth and all lumps are removed.
Serve with fresh strawberries, melons or grapes on fruit tray.

title: protein snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into walnut size balls and store in refrigerator.

title: blueberry supreme
directions: Layer 1:
Combine softened margarine and flour.
Smooth into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: double corn muffins
directions: Mix cornmeal with buttermilk; let stand.
Stir flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir in Egg Beaters, corn syrup, chilies and Mexicorn.
Mix until just blended.
Grease or spray 12-cup muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 12 servings; each contains 170 calories and 1 g fat.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger, onion, green pepper, tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, eggs and mushrooms together in heavy pan for 3 hours, until thick.
Prepare noodles as package directs; drain.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, arrange noodles, one layer at a time.
Top with meat mixture, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: christmas relish
directions: Grind mangoes and onions.
Add salt and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes then drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar and mustard seed with mangoes and onions.
Boil 3 minutes.
Chop celery last.
Stir in good.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: flank steak teriyaki barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak and pour over flank steak. Marinate 8 hours or overnight.
Turn occasionally.
Barbecue steak over hot coals, turning once until done, about 8 minutes on each side for medium rare.
Baste occasionally while grilling.
Carve slices thin, cutting on diagonal from top to bottom of steak.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in large skillet.
Add peppers and carrot; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce; add to pan with pineapple, juice, vinegar, brown sugar and ginger.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Add chicken and cook for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: caramel coffee cake
directions: Put the bread dough in a greased pan, 9 x 9-inch.
Mix the margarine, sugar, cream and pudding and pour over the bread pieces.
If desired, sprinkle the mix with cinnamon and ground nutmeg.
Let the dough rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brittany's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix all together in large pan.
Let raise 1 hour; stir down and let rise again.
Pour out onto floured board.
Roll out.
Add cinnamon, sugar and butter (just cover it).
Roll up, cut and let rise.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Break pretzels in 9 x 13-inch dish (unsalted can be used). Heat butter and 1 tablespoon sugar; bring to boil and pour over pretzels.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes; cool.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar; mix in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour over pretzels. Boil 2 cups water and Jell-O; add frozen strawberries in syrup. Cool until slightly thickened and pour over pretzels.
Add Cool Whip and grated pretzels for topping.

title: christmas morning surprise
directions: Cook sauce until well done and crumble well.
Drain on paper towels and set aside.
Spread each slice of bread on both sides with soft butter.

title: gravy pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops in skillet.
Drain off fat. Place in a 9 x 13-inch cooking dish.
Mix soups and pour over chops.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 45 to 50 minutes. Remove foil during last 10 minutes.

title: apples-plus salad
directions: Drain the mandarin oranges.
Combine all ingredients and garnish with apple slices and a dash of paprika.

title: linda's italian cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll out and cut into shapes.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: hot crab appetizer
directions: Mix everything together except almonds.
Spoon mixture into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers or icebox rye.

title: pantry chicken bisque soup
directions: Boil together above ingredients.
Drain off stock.
Debone chicken and chop meat, set aside.
Put veggies through a sieve or blender and set aside.
In separate pan, melt 1 cup butter and add 1 cup flour to it (a roux).
Stir until it has a shiny look, then it's ready.
Put liquid back on stove on low heat.
Add thickened roux and stir and simmer 15 minutes until soup become shiny.
Add veggies and chicken.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo in small pan.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb-upside down cake
directions: Cut up rhubarb in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with strawberry or raspberry jello.
Spread on sugar and marshmallows.
Mix cake mix as directed and spread.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour. Cool in pan 5 minutes, then remove to tray or platter.

title: lela's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and peanut butter.
Work flour and soda in.
Pinch off in size of egg.
Put in pan and mash out with fork.

title: becky's chicken casserole
directions: Mix oleo, 2 tablespoons poppy seeds and crushed crackers. (Save enough of this mixture to sprinkle on top of casserole.) Put this mixture in bottom of 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Add chicken on top of this.
Make a sauce of soups, sour cream and 1 tablespoon of poppy seeds.
Mix well, but do not heat or cook. Pour over chicken.
Top casserole with oleo, poppy seeds and crushed cracker mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: deviled ham nut ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill well.
Form into a ball and roll in mixture of 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1/2 cup chopped parsley to coat completely.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Let ground cranberries, orange and sugar mixture set overnight.
Soak plain gelatin in cold water and add to cherry gelatin and warm water mixture.
When it starts to gel, add pecans, apples, celery and cranberry mixture.
Refrigerate until well set.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: vegetables marinara
directions: Place rice in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cook vegetables until tender-crisp; drain. Spoon over rice. Top with marinara sauce. Cover and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Combine cheeses. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more to melt cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Be careful not to get too much juice from yams.
Cover top with marshmallows and bake at 325° until marshmallows are brown, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown the ground beef and add rest of ingredients. Cook slowly 1 hour or longer. Serve over spaghetti and top with grated Parmesan.

title: deep-fried vegetable batter
directions: Mix egg and milk together.
Add cornmeal; mix well.
Add flour and salts together with egg mixture.
Add Accent; mix well. Should be thin batter.
Dip cut up vegetables in batter; deep fry at 350° until golden brown.

title: elephant stew(very tasty)
directions: Cut elephant meat into bite size chunks.
This will take two months.
Cut vegetables into cubes (another two months).
Place meat in pan and cover with 1000 gallons of brown gravy.
Simmer 4 weeks.
Shovel in salt and pepper to taste.
When meat is tender, add veggies.
A steam shovel is useful in this.
Simmer slowly 4 more weeks.
Garnish with parsley.
Will serve 3,500 people.
If more is expected, add the two rabbits.
This is not recommended, as very few people like hare in their stew.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Crumble and set aside.
Saute onion in margarine.
Cook potatoes in water until done.
Add sausage.
Take off heat and add can of milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to boiling.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Stir together sugar, butter, crisco and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, and cocoa.
Mix well then add milk and vanilla. Pour into a tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: fancy garden blend
directions: Cover the first 6 ingredients in a large plastic container with ice water. Stir occasionally. When all ice is melted, drain. Place in large pot on stove.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour over vegetable mixture. Bring back to a boil and continue simmering as you fill jars.
Put tops on and seal. Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: brownie pie
directions: Cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg until smooth; set aside.
Spread 1/2 brownie mix in bottom of crust, adding to brownie mix, oil, 1 tablespoon water and 2 eggs.
Beat 50 strokes. Spoon cream cheese over brownie layer.
Top with remaining brownie mix; spread evenly and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until center is puffed and crust golden brown.
Place hot fudge in microwave bowl and microwave for 30 seconds.
Stir in remaining tablespoon water and drizzle fudge over top of pie.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add two sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: crock-pot barbecue ribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs with salt and pepper.
Place ribs in broiler pan under broiler for 30 minutes to brown and remove excess fat. Slice ribs into serving size pieces and put in crock-pot.
Add onion.
Pour in barbecue sauce.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).

title: tomato meat sauce
directions: In a large nonstick pan, cook beef and sausage until brown. Drain off fat.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, basil, onion, garlic and parsley.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and paste with water.
Stir well.
Add sauce mix and oleo.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti or noodles.
May sprinkle with grated cheese if desired.

title: sour cream and green bean soup
directions: Saute onion and chunked potatoes in oleo.
Add 1 quart water. Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add green beans with juice and milk.
Do not boil from this point on.
With electric mixer, beat the sour cream and flour.
Introduce a little hot liquid at a time to sour cream mixture.
Add slowly to soup.
Stir for 5 minutes, until flour is cooked in.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Again, do not boil.
Makes approximately 2 quarts of soup.
A meatless delight!

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together for 2 minutes. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13 inch dish. While still hot, prick cake with fork and cover with 2 cups powdered sugar, grated lemon rind and juice of 2 lemons.

title: scalloped onions
directions: In a buttered baking dish at 400 cook whole Onions.
Cut Onions into quarters; add Salt and Pepper.
Mix grated Cheese with Cream Sauce or Soup.
Bake at 400 until brown.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chips, and spread in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Refrigerate.

title: polvoron
directions: *For best results, use "KLIM" powdered milk.

title: corned beef
directions: Remove meat from package.
Wash and simmer for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove from pan and place on rack (fat side down). Score meat on both sides.
Mix brown sugar and mustard together and spread over both sides of meat.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs and beat.
Sift together cake flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add with buttermilk. Add in flavorings and vinegar last.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Check for doneness.

title: cabbage beef casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Put chopped cabbage all across pan.
Brown meat.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Mix meat, cooked rice and onion rings.
Spoon this mixture over cabbage.
Mix soup and water and pour all over casserole.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients; spread in a 9-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Place cut up chicken in baking pan, sprinkle with paprika. Bake in hot oven until well browned on all sides.
Take quartered onion and boil in water until tender.
Pour soup and drained cooked onions over chicken, bake until well heated, serve with rice.

title: low-fat apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and prepare tube pan with Pam.
Mix apples, NutraSweet and fructose.
Let stand for 1 hour, stirring often.
Mix raisins, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well (do not use mixer). Mix in apple mixture and pour into the tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole ii
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cook in boiling, salted water until just tender.
Drain and cool.
In a small pan, saute onion and butter until golden brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels margarine and 3 Tbsp. sugar.
Press in 9x13 pan and bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Allow to cool.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Mix white sugar and evaporated milk in pot and boil for 6 minutes, then pour over remaining ingredients. Beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes. Pour into greased Pyrex bowl; let cool and cut into squares.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt butter.
Blend with cocoa and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Add flour and vanilla; stir well. Bake, in oblong baking pan which has been sprayed with cooking spray, for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
While still hot, smooth on top of cake the marshmallow cream.
Let set for a few minutes. Pour Chocolate Frosting over marshmallow cream.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken).
Stir gently.
Pour into Dutch oven.
Place chicken on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for at least 2 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Place in a pan of hot water and bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Will make a custard top.

title: catfish with strawberries
directions: In a saucepan, combine the wine, orange juice, margarine and spices.
Place the fish in the mixture and simmer for about 10 minutes or until opaque.
Remove from liquid.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Combine with egg, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Chill the dough.
Make into small balls and press down.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Press down with flat bottom cup dipped in sugar.

title: saucy-sweet ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving-size pieces; place in large Dutch oven. Add enough water to cover ribs; cover and simmer over low heat 45 minutes.
Drain ribs and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients; stir well.
Spoon sauce over ribs; cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ribs
directions: Bake ribs on rack at 450° for half hour.
Drain off fat. Sprinkle on seasoning.
Finish baking at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 2 days.
Before serving, garnish with pimentos.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon into thirds and wrap water chestnuts. Secure with toothpicks. Bake 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Mix rest of ingredients to make sauce. Drizzle over bacon wrapped chestnuts. Bake 30 minutes more.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Season slightly with salt and pepper.
Mix soups with water in a large cup.
In a 3-quart crock-pot, put 1/2 meat, 1/2 Tater Tots and pour 1/3 of soup mixture over this.
Add rest of meat and Tater Tots.
Pour 2/3 of soup mixture over top.
Cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: 2-layer fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Boil for 4 minutes; remove from heat.
Add 1/2 jar of Marshmallow Creme, chocolate chips and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
