Mix until Marshmallow Creme and chocolate chips are melted.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: Melt sugar in water.
Add all other ingredients (except ginger ale).
Freeze in 2 1/2-gallon containers.
Remove from freezer 3 hours before serving.
When slushy, pour ginger ale over and serve.

title: choco-banana bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, egg and bananas.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Brown meat.
Put in slow cooker and add cream of chicken soup.
Mix.
Stir every hour or so.
Use with potatoes or rice or noodles.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Pour crunched Oreos into bottom of bowl.
Pack down.
In separate bowl, melt and mix the cream cheese and margarine.
Add chocolate pudding mix and milk.
Mix well.
Add whipped topping to mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Pour mixture onto packed Oreo crumbs.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Serve frozen or defrost for 1/2 hour.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, uncooked rice, onion, garlic, salt and pepper together with 3 tablespoons of tomatoes out of the can.
Steam cabbage leaves until wilted enough to roll.
Then roll meat mixture into small patties inside the cabbage leaves and pin with toothpicks.
Place in heavy covered skillet or pot and pour remaining tomatoes over the cabbage rolls.
Steam for about an hour.

title: banana torte
directions: Combine 1/2 cup pecans, the margarine and flour.
Press evenly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and half of the whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.

title: saucy chicken casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, combine soups, sour cream, wine or broth, onion and seasonings.
Arrange chicken on top of sauce. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve chicken and sauce over noodles or rice.
Garnish with parsley.

title: may bec's hot rolls(city school roll recipe)
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix 4 tablespoons sugar, salt, oil, 1 cup warm water and 2 cups flour.
Add the egg and mix well. Add yeast mixture and mix.
Add in approximately 2 cups of flour to make a soft dough.
Rest dough in a greased bowl.
Cover with a wet cloth.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and shape into 36 rolls. Set on greased sheet and let rise again, covered.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes until brown.
Dough may be refrigerated for several days and frozen up to 3 months.
Takes about 2 hours to rise with this method.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix ingredients and let sit in greased pan for 15 minutes. Bake for 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve warm.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate. Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Beat 3/4 cup sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Stir together 2 cups flour and baking powder. Add flour mixture and milk alternately to beaten mixture; beat until smooth after each addition.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Top with blueberries.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Take skin off chicken.
Put chicken in pan.
Pour mixture over it.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off and let chicken stay in oven for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: dill pickels
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in jars, add the next 4 ingredients. Combine water, vinegar and salt mixture. Bring to a boil. Pour over cucumbers. Seal. Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: linda's fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients together. Also delicious as a topping for ice cream.

title: green chile chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, onions, broth, soups and green chiles. Grease 9 x 11-inch glass dish.
Layer tortillas, chicken mixture and grated cheese.
Repeat layering until mixture is used up.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and egg; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool slightly.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Add plenty of faith and mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve everybody you meet daily, include self.

title: cora's jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil the raisins and the water together for 3 minutes.
Set aside (do not drain).
Cream together shortening and the sugar. Add eggs and raisins with liquid and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift remaining ingredients and add.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Drop by a tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix everything except cheese and chilies.
Put 1/2 corn mixture in casserole.
Top with 3/4 cup cheese and 1 can mashed chilies.
Repeat for second layer.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 350°. Sprinkle remaining cup of cheese over top when casserole is taken out of oven.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine Cool Whip, sour cream, lemon juice and sugar; mix well. Add other ingredients; stir well. Keep frozen.

title: chicken and sausage
directions: Pierce sausage with a fork several times.
Place sausage in a small frying pan; cook over low heat for about 20 minutes to render fat.
Drain on paper towels.
Slice into 1-inch chunks. Place flour, pepper and paprika in a plastic bag.
Add chicken pieces, a few at a time; shake to coat.
Reserve flour mixture. In a Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook until brown, 5 minutes a side.
Remove and drain on paper towels. Add onion and mushrooms; cook until tender.
Stir in the remaining seasoned flour.
Return chicken to the pan.
Add 1/2 cup water, the tomatoes with their juices and caraway seed.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in sausage and peas to cook 10 minutes longer, or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: sage dressing
directions: Cut skirt steak into strips.
Marinate in glass dish for 24 hours in pineapple juice.
Stir once or twice while marinating. Discard pineapple juice.
Marinate 24 hours in glass dish in Italian dressing.
Reserve dressing.
Drain.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, oregano, coriander seed and cumin.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup margarine; stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add cocoa mixture; beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup Eagle Brand, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until cake springs back.
In small saucepan, melt remaining 1/4 cup margarine, 1/4 cup cocoa and Eagle Brand.
Stir in powdered sugar and nuts. Spread on warm cake.

title: bean soup with noodles
directions: Soak beans in salted water overnight; drain.
In soup kettle, combine beans, ham bone, vegetables and bay leaf.
Add enough cold water to cover.
Bring to a boil, skim both from surface and reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until beans are tender.
Add more water as needed to keep broth covering beans.
Discard ham bone and bay leaf.
Cut off any meat left on the ham.
Cool soup slightly.
Puree half the beans in a blender.
Pour them back into the soup kettle.
Add half the beans in a blender.
Pour them back into the soup kettle.
Add the meat. Bring soup to boil, then add broken noodles.
Cook for an additional 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Ladle into soup bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water and dissolve over low heat.
Fold into cheese.
Add chopped celery, mayonnaise, grated onion and shrimp.
Season to taste.
Pour into oiled fish mold and chill until firm.
Serve with crackers of your choice.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables; add first eight ingredients together.
In shaker, add vinegar, sugar, oil, pepper and dill weed.
Pour dressing over vegetables. Let set 12 to 24 hours. Keeps 10 days to 2 weeks.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, salt, sugar & milk and bring to a boil, or until thick. Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla.

title: celery dressing(low-fat)
directions: Chop onion and celery.
Saute in turkey fat.
Prepare Melba toast.
Cube and stir in broth.
Add marjoram, salt, pepper and sauteed vegetables.
Add well beaten egg.
Coat casserole dish with vegetable pan spray.
Spoon mixture into casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the dressing is puffy.

title: first place chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs and margarine, mixing well.
Pour into 1 (3-quart) oblong casserole, 2 (1 1/2-quart casseroles, or 3 (1-quart) casseroles.
Combine melted margarine and bread crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and hot.

title: veal piccata
directions: Dust scallops with flour, salt and pepper.
Heat 4 tablespoons butter plus 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat until bubbly.
Quickly brown veal, about 2 minutes each side. Remove to a warm platter and cover loosely with skillet cover. Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Add lemon juice and parsley to skillet.
Remove from heat and swirl in remaining butter.
Arrange veal over noodles.
Pour butter sauce over all.
Garnish with lemon slices and parsley.
Serves 2.

title: carolina delights
directions: Combine
sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in a saucepan and bring
to
boil over medium heat.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Add oats,
peanut butter and vanilla; mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax or	plastic wrap or pour all into 8 x 10-inch cake pan to form squares.
Cool at room temperature or place in refrigerator.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: layered salad deluxe
directions: Layer spinach, lettuce, eggs, bacon, water chestnuts and peas in that order.
Combine sour cream, dressing mix and mayonnaise. Mix well and spread over top of vegetables, sealing to the edge of bowl.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Cover tightly and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss gently before serving.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: hamburger meat doritos casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Blend remaining items in saucepan.
Layer with meat and cheese and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover last 5 minutes.

title: basic muffins with variations
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl, stirring until just moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburg chowder
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and seasonings.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, honey, mustard and paprika together and boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add celery seed and celery salt, onion juice and vegetable oil.
Beat or shake vigorously.
Serve with any fresh or frozen fruit salad.
It's especially good on a salad of romaine lettuce and fresh grapefruit sections.
If refrigerated, shake before using.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Combine these ingredients in pot and boil for 1 minute. Remove from stove.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 cups of quick oats.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper and let cool for 30 minutes.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Spread in ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeats, if desired.
Mix next 3 ingredients. Sprinkle over nuts.
Pour boiling water over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Good with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: martha's egg custard pie
directions: Set
pie crust out to thaw while mixing custard filling. Check to make sure all cracks are smoothed shut.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat
eggs.	Scald milks.
Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch together.
Add to eggs while beating on low speed.	Add vanilla, then
milk	slowly.
Mix
well.
Pour
into pie shell slowly. Bake
at 450° for 5 minutes;
425° for 5 minutes; 375° for	10 minutes; then reduce temperature to 325° and bake until center
of pie
is
set.
Test by shaking pie slightly.
Ovens vary
so you may have to reduce temperatures by 5°or so.
Don't burn.
Dot
top with
butter.
(First
time
ever sharing this recipe.)

title: kristi's chicken wings
directions: Use one bag cut up chicken wings. Fry chicken wings in grease for 10 to 12 minutes or until done. Cook all ingredients until well blended.
Place chicken wings in sauce and cook 2 to 3 minutes.

title: scrambled eggs with tomatoes
directions: Beat eggs; add salt.
Heat 4 tablespoons oil in pan and pour in eggs.
Stir quickly and constantly until scrambled.
Heat remaining 4 tablespoons oil in another pan.
Add tomatoes and saute until bubbly.
Mix with eggs and add sugar.
Stir well and serve.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Brown chicken and drain off oil.
Cook broccoli just until firm and drain.
Place broccoli in bottom of casserole.
Place browned chicken on top.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown meat.
Mix corn, beans, potatoes, brown gravy mix and onion gravy mix. Bring to a boil. Add cooked meat. Add water, if necessary. Simmer until potatoes are done.

title: elaine's cheese dip
directions: Pour Ro-Tel in a saucepan. Add cheese and stir until smooth and cheese is melted, then add mushroom soup and mix well. Add chili and stir until smooth.

title: easy pizza dough
directions: Cut flour and margarine together as for pie crust.
Dissolve yeast in warm water thoroughly and add to flour and margarine.
Mix well.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the large oven bag into a baking pan.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce to the bag.
Add pineapple and green pepper to the bag.
Last, add the chicken breasts.
Make sure chicken is coated with the sauce.
Bake until chicken is tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: coffee shop corn muffins
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, sugars, baking soda and salt. Beat egg separately with buttermilk and oil; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 425 for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut off top of green peppers.
Remove seeds and membrane.
Boil peppers in salted water 5 minutes; drain.
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add rice, water, garlic powder, salt, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes, oregano and basil.
Cover and cook until rice soaks up liquid and is tender.
Stir egg substitute, peas and cheese into rice mixture.
Stuff green peppers and stand upright in baking dish. Bake for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: appletts
directions: Combine gelatine with 1/4 cup applesauce.
Let set 5 minutes. Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add gelatine.
Boil 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add walnuts just before removing from heat.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch pan that has been buttered and dusted with powdered sugar.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares and shake in sack of powdered sugar to coat.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Heat slowly, stirring until smooth.
Add one No. 2 can drained Shoe Peg corn.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix together all ingredients and fold in the Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Beat well. Add salt and vanilla; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour into a greased tube pan; place in a cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until done.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Mix meal and flour, add milk and egg.
Then add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a hot skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake in three layers at 350° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Completely cool layers and frost.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
When done, add milk and butter to make mashed potatoes; salt to season.
Add diced onions, sliced boiled eggs, sliced dill pickles and a little pickle juice.
Stir all together and serve while hot.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook eggs, salt, vinegar, juice and flour together until thick.
Pour over other mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill at least 24 hours before serving.

title: meat loaves with spaghetti sauce
directions: Stir together 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, ground beef, breadcrumbs, onion, egg, salt and pepper until just combined. Shape mixture into 2 (8-inch) loaves and place in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: asparagus potato bake
directions: In large heavy skillet, cook potatoes in butter and oil until potatoes are fork tender.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 9-inch pie place.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove foil and continue cooking for about 5 minutes. If desired, sprinkle a little cheese over top for the last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: marie's chicken ravioli casseroles
directions: Use 2 (9 x 13-inch) casserole dishes.
Cook noodles (I use chicken bouillon).
Saute onion, pepper, celery and garlic in butter.
Add chopped chicken, soup and
pimento.
Add broth. Layer noodles, then chicken mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly.
Freezes well.
Serves 20.

title: southwestern egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place thawed hash browns, enough to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, between paper towel layers and gently blot any water left from thawing process.
Cover the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with has browns.
Bake for about 10 minutes, then remove from oven.
Top hash browns evenly with sausage, tomatoes and cheese.
Whip eggs with sour cream, half and half or milk, green chiles and salt.
Pour over casserole.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until egg mixture is not runny.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the rice, cream soups, 1/2 package soup mix and the water. Combine in a large, deep casserole dish.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of mixture.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 package of soup mix over chicken.
Cover with casserole lid or tinfoil; bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: velvet cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients, then add shortening, vanilla and 2/3 cup milk.
Beat two minutes, then add remaining 1/3 cup milk and eggs.
Beat two minutes more.
Bake in 350° oven in layer or loaf pans.

title: nora's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat oven to 375° to 400°.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.
Best if cooked in iron skillet.

title: salmon patties
directions: Open the can of salmon and remove the bones.
Add onion, egg, grated cheese, butter, milk and equal amounts of flour and corn meal to thicken the mixture so it will stick together.
Put small amount of cooking oil in a skillet and spoon out patties and cook until golden brown.

title: ribbon fantasy fudge
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in pan.
Bring to a full boil; stir constantly.
Boil 4 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add 1 cup (1/2 jar) Marshmallow Creme and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Repeat steps with remaining ingredients, substituting peanut butter for chocolate chips.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds. This recipe can be doubled.

title: double-crisp chicken
directions: Measure crushed Kellogg's corn flakes into shallow dish or pan.
Set aside.

title: mushroom burgers dijon
directions: Form turkey into 4 patties, seasoning with salt and pepper. Cook in nonstick pan sprayed with "Pam."
Cook until brown on both sides.
Remove and keep warm.
Deglaze pan with wine, mustard and tarragon.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
To serve, place burgers on toasted bread.
Spoon mushroom mixture over top. Serves 2 to 4.
Low-fat.

title: hot nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of casserole dish, then top with chili, then cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: italian lemon ice
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Boil 4 cups water and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice. Add softened gelatin to syrup and stir until dissolved. Put in individual cups and freeze 3 hours.

title: corned beef casserole(an easy and economical dish)
directions: Combine all ingredients except
crumbs.
Pour
into a 2 quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbs or chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: lentil soup
directions: Heat butter.
When hot, add celery and onion; cover and cook 3 minutes over medium heat.
Add carrot, spices and garlic; cover and continue cooking.
Add lentils and chicken stock.
Season well and mix.
Bring to a boil.
Cook soup, partially covered, 2 hours over low heat.
Twenty minutes before soup is finished, add rice and finish cooking.
Serve.

title: marshmallow marble top fudge
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil; set aside.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons butter with sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together. Cream together shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar and sugar. Add egg to creamed mixture. Beat together and add milk and vanilla. Add dry ingredients to the wet. Mix well. Roll dough into small balls and roll in sugar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 minutes at 350°. Remove cookie sheet from oven and add 1 Hershey's Kiss to the center of each cookie. Return to oven for 5 minutes. Cool.

title: special tea meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
In a large shallow baking pan, shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Boil potato quarters in enough water to cover for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender when pierced with a knife. When cool enough, peel potatoes and place in mixing bowl. In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine vinegar, relish, mustard, salt and black pepper. Shake well, then add oil and shake again. Toss warm potatoes with dressing; add onions and red pepper. Serve warm or chilled.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; mix well. Add zucchini and mix. Sift in dry ingredients; beat well. Stir in lemon rind. Grease and flour two bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Cut off crusts and roll out slices of bread until very thin. Saute chopped onion and mushrooms in butter.
Mix with cream cheese.
Spread bread slices.
Roll up like jelly roll and cut each slice into 3 pieces.
Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, vanilla, salt, peanut butter and milk. Roll into balls and put on wax paper.
Chill 2 hours.
Melt chips and wax over hot water.
Coat peanut butter balls with chocolate. Refrigerate.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix and sugar.
Add beer.
Knead a few times.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with floured cutter.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 9 biscuits.
(May be baked in greased muffin pans.)

title: chicken captain
directions: Remove skin from chicken;
flour
and brown in shortening. Remove from shortening and keep warm.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush the cookies and set aside. In a bowl, combine the margarine, cream cheese and 10x sugar and mix well. In a second bowl, combine the Cool Whip, pudding and milk and mix well. Combine the two bowls. Line a new flowerpot with foil (or use a child's sand bucket and shovel). Or use a bowl. Alternately layer the cookies and other mixture, making sure the top layer is cookies. If you wish, decorate with an artificial flower to make it look more realistic.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies, mix with margarine.
Press into pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over crushed cookies. Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Beat chocolate pudding and milk until thick. Spread on cheese mixture and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: hot dip
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in skillet and set aside.
In saucepan, melt cheese with tomatoes and soup.
(If time allows, use slow cooker.)
Then add the meat mixture and keep in slow cooker until time to serve.

title: southern chicken fricassee
directions: Melt butter.
Fry butter and flour in sauce pan on medium heat till dark brown.
Immediately add water and stir till smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat until chicken is tender. You can either cook dumplings in the fricassee gravy or serve over cooked rice.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Preheat oven.
Mix Bisquick, water and cheese.
Drop by large spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
After baking, brush on butter mixed with seasonings.

title: diabetic chicken salad(contains 309 calories)
directions: Dice the chicken and celery.
Mix together and season to taste.
Add mayonnaise, mixing well.
Serve on a lettuce leaf. Garnish with a slice of olive.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep sealed in an airtight container.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons (to your taste) to each one cup of boiling water.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt margarine.
Brown meat and add soup, pepper, garlic salt, salt and tomato sauce.
Set aside.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with grated cheese.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Pour over fruit salad or over pineapple, watermelon and blueberries.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in a large casserole dish.

title: individual olive salads
directions: Slice
olives
from pits.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and bring to
a
boil.	Remove	from
heat and add to gelatin. Moisten in	water and stir to dissolve.
Pour hot mixture over beaten eggs,
stirring
briskly.
Add
horseradish,
mustard, onion salt, lemon juice, carrots, fresh fruit and olives. Stir to blend.
Cool until thick but not firm.	Add mayonnaise and stir.
Pour into individual molds.
Chill until firm and serve on salad greens.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour melted margarine into casserole type baking dish.
Pour in batter and sprinkle blueberries on top.
Bake until lightly browned at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cornbread crumbs and 1/2 stick margarine. Place 1/2 of this mixture in a greased casserole. Mix the squash with the remaining ingredients and pour over the cornbread crumbs. Top with the remaining cornbread crumbs and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a bowl.
Melt chocolate over boiling water and add to cream mixture.
Add vanilla and add 1 egg, then beat with electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and melted butter.
Pour into 8 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining 2 eggs, powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Pour over chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
This will fill 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1-quart prepared sauce (I prefer Ragu with mushrooms) and bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: thanksgiving cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water. Add other ingredients and chill.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup of mix to 3/4 cup of boiling water.

title: souped-up broccoli
directions: Cook the broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook the carrots for 10 minutes.
Drain.
In a buttered 2-quart casserole arrange a layer of half the broccoli then a layer of 1/2 the carrots. Repeat.
Cover the vegetables with the undiluted mushroom soup. Top with the grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread pudding
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Beat eggs and add all other ingredients.
Pour into buttered dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in oven at 350°.
Very easy and great with stew or barbecues.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Place 8 pepperoni slices on each rectangle.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Starting at shortest side, tightly roll up each rectangle and pinch to seal. Slice each roll into 4 equal pieces.
Pinch dough together on one side of each slice to seal.
Place sealed side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with pizza sauce.

title: chuck steak supper
directions: Place the steak in the center of a large piece of aluminum foil and sprinkle with the soup mix and steak sauce.
Cover the steak with the vegetables and dot with oleo.
Sprinkle with salt. Fold foil over steak mixture and seal securely.
Place in a baking pan and bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: celery seed dressing for cabbage
directions: Heat and pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.

title: spanish style chicken and rice
directions: Pat
chicken
quite
dry.
Season
with salt and pepper. Heat oil
and
fry chicken until golden brown; remove chicken. Add bacon and cook 1 minute; add onion, garlic and peppers and cook until tender.
Add
rice
to
pan (more oil as necessary); add paprika, cayenne
and
black pepper and toss rice well over moderate heat until coated with vegetables mixture.
Add stock, bay leaf, saffron or turmeric, tomatoes and chicken;
season to taste.
Bring
to boil; cover, turn down heat and simmer for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
In a bowl mix hash browns, sour cream and 1 1/2 cups cheese, salt and pepper, 1/2 can of Durkee onions and soup.
Mix well and put in a large baking dish. Put pork chops on top.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Then remove foil and put the rest of the cheese and onions on top.
Bake for 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: tomato-onion hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil in a medium bowl.
Stir until smooth; set aside for 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, chicken, celery, mayo, and soup together and place in a greased 1 quart casserole dish.
Cover with corn flakes or almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Casserole freezes well!

title: tangy spinach l'orange(makes 4 dozen appetizers)
directions: In small bowl, combine oranges, onion, oil, vinegar, mustard and sugar; set aside.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt sugar with hot water; add liquid smoke and catsup.

title: chunky cinnamon applesauce
directions: Cook apples over medium to low heat for 20 minutes or until tender. Mash the apples. Add sugar and candies. Cook, uncovered, until sugar and candies are dissolved. Remove from heat. Cool. Refrigerate until serving. Yields 6 cups. Very good.

title: dump cake
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2 pan, layer the pineapple and pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Over cake mix sprinkle pecans.
Cut margarine into patties and place on top of nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350.
Serve with cool whip, ice cream or just plain.

title: rice-creamed corn
directions: Cook rice in water, butter and salt, then add creamed corn. Bring to a boil.
Set on very low and cover for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, cut and arrange apples in large Corning Ware dish. Sprinkle lemon juice over all the apples.
In a small bowl, cream together the margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add the oatmeal and flour to make topping.
Sprinkle crumb topping over the apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Split wings at joint; discard tips and pat dry.
Deep fry at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or bake in a roasting pan at 425° for 1 hour.
Turn halfway through cooking time.
Combine sauce and butter.
Dip wings in sauce to coat completely.
Do not allow chicken to soak in sauce (chicken may become soggy).
(My personal favorite is:
Grill outdoors instead of deep frying.
Gives a great smoky flavor.)

title: golden goodie bars
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 30 minutes at 350°, until done.
Very good.

title: nut cookie crust
directions: Mix butter or margarine and brown sugar in large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients until crumbly. Press mixture against bottom and sides of a 9 x 1 1/2-inch pie pan.

title: creamy corn chowder
directions: Combine frozen potatoes, onion, margarine and water in 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cover and reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and corn.
Bring to simmering point.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice
directions: Put rice, mushrooms and onion in pan and brown.
Add soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Add broth and cook until rice is cooked and broth is gone.

title: mulled cider
directions: Stir ingredients over low heat for 20 minutes.
Do not boil. Remove sticks and cloves.
Serve hot.

title: apricot tea ring
directions: Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until thickened, about 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: speckled butter bean chowder
directions: Heat butter in large heavy saucepan.
Cook onion, carrots and celery until softened, but not browned, about 5 minutes.
Add butter beans with liquid.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to
a boil.
Simmer on low heat 15 to 20 minutes or longer.
This chowder may be prepared ahead of time and reheated.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and mayonnaise, then add to this, vanilla. Dissolve soda in water.
Add soda, salt and flour to mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
This is very easy to make and is a delicious, moist cake.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit, nuts, dry cake mix in a large bowl. Beat eggs and milk and vanilla together. Blend with cake mix, fruit and nuts. Place pan of water on bottom rack of oven. Bake at 325° for two hours. Wrap in foil while still warm.

title: potatoes in sauce
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters lengthwise.
Cover with water; add onion and salt and bring to a boil.
When tender, do not drain.
Melt Crisco|.
Blend in flour and add to potatoes.
Add pepper and let simmer for about 5 minutes more until flour is cooked.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown beef and chopped onion in skillet.
Drain off grease. Season to taste.
Spread beans in bottom of glass baking dish (oblong).
Top with beef and onions.
Sprinkle chili peppers on top of beef.
Cover with cheese.
Cover cheese with taco sauce. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with green onions and olives.
Put avocado dip in the center with sour cream on top. Serve with chips.
Best if served warm.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on greased jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out the pastry and fit it into a nine-inch pie plate.
Combine the sour cream, egg, lemon juice and flour.
Fold in the sliced apples and place the mixture in the pastry shell.
Either full or strips for top shell.
Cook one hour at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat with taco seasoning, water, and salsa. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: easy rocky road
directions: Place chocolate chips, butter and shortening in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50%) for 5 to 7 minutes or until chips are softened and mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Blend well.
Spread evenly in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cover; chill until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 16 squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Mix all ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake until bubbly and brown.

title: spicy cheese log
directions: Soften cheeses at room temperature.
Cream both cheeses together.
Add garlic powder and chili powder or I use a little less than 1/2 package of taco or nacho seasoning.
Blend well. Add chopped nuts (1 cup).
Shape into log.
May need to chill before shaping.
Roll in chili powder sprinkled on wax paper, then in chopped nuts.
Chill and serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In saucepan heat spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce in 13 x 9 baking dish and arrange 3 pieces uncooked pasta lengthwise over sauce.
Pour 1/2 cup sauce over pasta; spread with half cheese mixture.
Cover with 1/2 cup sauce and repeat layers.
Top with pasta and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cover with foil.	Bake 60 to 75 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese and let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add water slowly, stirring to dissolve ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter.

title: whipped icing
directions: Mix flour and milk to a smooth paste.
Be sure to get out all lumps.
Cook over low heat, stirring to keep out lumps.
Cool; add sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Whip until fluffy.

title: salad with vinaigrette dressing
directions: In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine the first 7 ingredients and shake well.
Toss salad greens and vegetables in a large bowl or arrange on individual salad plates.
Serve with dressing.
Yields 1 cup of dressing.

title: aunt laura's devil's food cake
directions: Mix cocoa in the flour.
Cream sugar and Crisco, salt and vanilla; add eggs and beat well.
Add soda to buttermilk and alternate with flour and cocoa; mix well.
Pour into 2 lined round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes until it tests done. Cool before icing.

title: apple crisp
directions: Layer apples in a pan.
Sprinkle lemon juice and water over apples.
Mix remaining ingredients for topping.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the meat and drain off grease.
Add the soup and sour cream.
Let this simmer while cooking the noodles.
Pour the cooked noodles into a small baking dish.
Add the meat mixture and bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Brown bacon in large pot.
Take out, crumble and return to pot.
Add
onions;	cook
until clear.
Add water and juice from clams.
Add potatoes and carrots; cook until tender.
Add cream, clams and
shrimp*.
Cook until sauce thickens or until you can't wait anymore.
Tastes better if aged overnight!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all together.
Serve chilled.
Can use any Italian dressing you like and add as much or as little of each of the ingredients.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saut the meat, onion and peppers. Grease iron skillet and sprinkle bottom with cornmeal, then pour in 1/2 cornbread mixture. Top with 1/2 pound rat cheese (grated), then add meat mixture and top with remaining cornmeal mixture. Cook at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tiny cinnamon rolls
directions: Unroll crescent dough; separate into 4 rectangles.
Pinch seals to seal.
Stir together sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over all 4 rectangles.
Roll up (jelly roll fashion).
Start with a long side; press edges to seal.
Cut each log into 5 slices. Place in lightly greased 8-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: sauce piquant
directions: Use 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup oil to make medium roux.
Stir onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic into roux and brown 10 minutes.
Stir tomato sauce, Ro-Tel tomatoes, V-8 juice and water into other mixture and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in tasso and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in smoked sausage, cut up fryer and 1 cup chopped green onions.
Simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is done. If you want it hot, add red pepper to taste.

title: frozen watermelon margaritas
directions: Place melon chunks in a bag and freeze until solid.
Run a lime wedge along the rim of a large stemmed cocktail glass.
Dip the moistened rim in the salt.
Set the lime wedge and the glass aside. Repeat with remaining wedges and 3 glasses.
Transfer about 3/4 of the melon chunks, separating them into a blender jar.
Add the tequila, Triple sec and lime juice.
Blend until fairly smooth. Add remaining melon and lend until smooth.
Divide mixture into glasses and squeeze a lime wedge into each.

title: garden salsa
directions: In medium size bowl combine all ingredients.
Toss gently but thoroughly to mix.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in pan and let bake for 2 hours.
Slice potatoes, carrots and onion up.
Put around chicken; add salt, pepper and seasoning salt.
Bake for 2 more hours at 350° to 400°.
Cover with foil.
When you put in pan, add 2 cups of water.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat together oleo and cream cheese.
Butter baking dish.
Add layer of spinach, then half of oleo and cream cheese mixture. Repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: banana split salad
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar. Stir in pineapple, strawberries and banana. Fold in cool whip and walnuts. Pour into a lightly sprayed 9 x 13 x 2 inch dish. Cover and freeze 3 hours or longer. Let sit 30 minutes before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together the oil and sugar.
Add the eggs and beat well with an electric mixer.

title: tortilla roll ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, beef, onions, garlic and salt.
Spread onto soft tortillas and roll up, placing into large ziploc bag or Tupperware container with lid.
Refrigerate overnight or for at least 3 hours.
Slice into 1/2 inch to 3/4 inch pieces just before serving with Picante sauce.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo. Beat eggs and add alternately with the milk. Add vanilla wafers, vanilla, coconut and pecans. Bake in shallow pan for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat until well mixed. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cover pan with Handi-Wrap.
When cooled, frost with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: maple flavored carrots
directions: Combine carrots, chile, salt and water in 2-quart pan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until carrots are tender and only 1 tablespoon of water remains.
Stir in butter, maple syrup and pepper to taste.
Makes 2 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together eggs, flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking soda and fruit cocktail.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute onions, bell peppers, and celery in butter. Add parsley and crawfish. Cook 10 minutes. Slowly add flour; add half and half cream and cheese. Add salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Cook noodles and drain. Mix everything together in a large baking dish. Bake until it bubbles.

title: easter egg candy
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and margarine.
Form into egg shapes. Let them set on waxed paper.
Coat them with dipping chocolate. Makes 15 eggs.
Can top with flower or nuts.

title: banana cream dessert
directions: Mix butter and flour.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Toss together and chill overnight.

title: venison pileau
directions: Fry bacon; drain off 3/4 of fat. Add onions and mushrooms; saute until done. Add venison and enough broth to cook; add salt and pepper. When meat is done, drain broth into large measuring cup. You will need 4 cups rice. If there is not enough, add more broth to make 4 cups (do not add water).

Put liquid back into pot; add instant coffee or Kitchen Bouquet; bring to boil. Add rice and let boil over medium heat for 7 minutes. Lower heat and cover until rice is done, about 20 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Put milk and butter on stove on low heat.
Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together in bowl, then add enough warm water to stir up to make a thick paste.
When butter has melted in skillet, add chocolate mix and turn up heat.
Stir until thick.
If too thick, add a little milk or water.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: white bread
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar.
Set aside until doubled. Meanwhile, mix additional water, sugar, melted margarine and salt. Add yeast mixture; stir in flour.
As dough gets stiffer, knead in additional flour.
Knead well.
Let dough raise twice, then form into loaves.
Makes six loaves.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: roast beef sandwiches
directions: Blend dressing mixes together, then cover roast with them. Heat in slow cooker for approximately 8 hours. Shred meat thoroughly before serving on buns of your choice.

title: sirloin tips en brochette
directions: Place meat in ungreased baking dish, 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch. Heat remaining ingredients except cornstarch to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. Cool.
Pour consomme mixture over meat.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours, turning meat occasionally.
Thread 4 or 5 cubes of meat on each of 6 to 8 skewers.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and butter. Add milk and flavoring.
Add coconut that has been combined with flour.
Bake at 325° until brown. Makes 6 pies.

title: creamy corn and vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Stir in reserved beet liquid, vinegar and butter.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 or 2 minutes more.
Stir in beets.
Cook and stir about 5 minutes more or until beets are heated through.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Flour and season boneless chicken breasts.
Fry in oil until done.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions. Place stuffing in casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts on top of stuffing.
Mix soup and milk and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dream side cake
directions: Bake orange cake mix as directed on box.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over top of baked cake.

title: hamburger patty stew
directions: Peel vegetables and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Form beef into 12 small flat patties.
In 2-quart casserole, layer half of patties, then half of vegetables, sprinkling with salt and pepper. Repeat.
Add water.
Press down into casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
When arranging the patties and vegetables on top layer, be sure that patties are fully covered to prevent scorching.
Microwave on Medium 25 to 28 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Reserve 1 cup cheese mixture.
Add pumpkin, remaining sugar and spices to remaining cheese mixture.
Mix well.

title: dried beef on rye
directions: Combine with enough mayonnaise to stick ingredients together. Spread on party rye.
Place under broiler to melt cheese and serve. Great flavor combination!

title: olive wills' pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening; beat in sugar gradually.
Stir in eggs and pumpkin.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 minutes to 1 hour.
Test with tester before removing from oven. Cool before slicing.

title: baked penne with sausage, zucchini and fontina
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2 1/2 to 3-quart deep casserole.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add sausage; break up while cooking.
Drain fat.
Transfer to bowl.
Add onion to skillet; saute about 5 minutes.
Add zucchini.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook until almost tender.
Add sausage to skillet.
Add cream, oregano, basil and red pepper flakes.
Bring to boil.
Add half of Fontina cheese and stir to melt.

title: squirrel recipe(three generations use)
directions: After squirrels are prepared for cooking, put them in plenty of water and boil until meat is tender.
Add onions and potatoes which have been chopped in large pieces.
Boil together 20 minutes then add tomatoes and corn.
Season well; let all this simmer until stew is quite thick and the meat has come to pieces.
It will take from one to two hours.
In the olden days, this stew was served with corn pone (corn bread).

title: hamburger salami
directions: Mix well.
Divide into three parts.
Put each portion into double plastic bags and close tightly.
Put in refrigerator for 3 days.
Each day, squeeze the bag to mix well.
On the 4th day, form into 6 rolls and lay across broiler pan.
Bake at 150° for 8 to 10 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until thread spins, then add raw peanuts and stir continuously after peanuts are added.
Cook until it turns a brownish gold.
Take from burner; add butter, salt and soda.
Mixture will boil up in pan quickly.
Pour onto buttered board to cool.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Crush Oreos and place in bottom of pan.
Pour melted butter over top.
Put a layer each of vanilla ice cream and fudge topping. Top off with layer of Cool Whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done and debone.
Save about 2 cups of chicken broth.
Moisten stuffing crumbs with broth and spread onto bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together in a bowl chicken, mushroom soup, vegetables and celery.
Pour over stuffing and spread in dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
"It's really good."

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: On bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, sprinkle marshmallows and walnuts.
Combine and pour over bottom the hot water, brown sugar and cocoa.
Mix chocolate cake according to package directions and pour over mixture in the bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: country-style ribs
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cut pork ribs into serving pieces if necessary.
Place ribs, meaty sides up, in ungreased rectangular pan.
Cover and bake about 2 hours or until tender and then drain. Heat remaining ingredients, stirring occasionally, until jelly is melted.
Pour over ribs.
Bake uncovered for about 30 minutes, spooning sauce over ribs occasionally, until ribs are hot.
Serve sauce over ribs, if desired.
Contains 455 calories per serving.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix dry gelatin and cake mix together.
Add remaining ingredients, adding eggs one at a time.
Bake in 3 greased and floured layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven-fried fish
directions: Combine corn flakes, celery, salt, onion salt, paprika and pepper.
Dip fish in milk, then roll in corn flake mixture.

title: low-fat walnut chicken(chinese)
directions: Mix oil, 2 teaspoons soy sauce and 1 teaspoon cornstarch in covered dish and mix chicken, refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Mix 1/2 broth, ginger, 3 teaspoons soy sauce and 2 teaspoons cornstarch.
Use to pour over remaining ingredients in microwave-proof bowl (or stir-fry) and cook until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Separately cook chicken until no longer pink and add to vegetables.
Heat all together, approximately 5 to 8 minutes, or until heated through.
Serve over cooked rice (which is simmered in 1/2 water and 1/2 broth).
Serves 4.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: You will need a clear, glass, deep dish casserole dish or glass lasagna pan.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk, stirring mixture as you pour it in.
Place on heat and cook slowly, stirring constantly, as it begins to thicken and boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from the heat.

title: impossible pie
directions: Grease pie plate; sprinkle zucchini, tomatoes, onion and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour into pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar - add eggs, soda, water, buttermilk, vanilla and salt.
Stir in bananas, flour and nuts.
Bake in bundt pan (or two layer pans) at 350 degrees for 40-50 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla together; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll out small portions of dough on lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cutters and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: squash pickles
directions: Place squash, onions and peppers in mixing bowl.
Sprinkle salt over this and let stand 1 to 2 hours; drain well.
Boil together vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and garlic. Add squash, onions and peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Place in clean jars and seal.

title: party bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with crispy tortilla chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: hawaiian supreme cake
directions: Sift cake mix and pudding together.
Add eggs, one at a time, then salad oil and 7-Up.
Mix.
Pour into 3 or 4 greased cake pans and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spiced date cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the dates and soda.
Let stand. Mix together the sugar, butter, eggs, cinnamon, allspice, cloves and salt.
Add together.
Beat in the flour and walnut meats. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done to the touch. Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar. Add eggs and bananas. Beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add to banana mixture, alternating with milk and vanilla. Beat well and add nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or bake in 2 small pans for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine ingredients, heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. If too thick, add more milk.
Eat with toast or thin cornbread.

title: season's best shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with vegetable dippers. Makes 2 cups.
Preparation time is 10 minutes plus chilling.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Use rolling pin and flatten each slice of decrusted bread. Spread each slice with cream cheese.
Roll up and take each roll and roll in melted margarine.
Then roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
These can be made ahead and frozen.

title: honey-baked chicken
directions: Baste chicken with orange juice and honey.
Bake in oven at 350° for about an hour.
Baste 2 to 3 times during the hour. The chicken has a glazed look when done.

title: barbecue tuna
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan breakfast rolls
directions: Grease bundt pan and add chopped nuts to bottom of pan. Place 18-20 frozen dinner rolls loosely around pan.
Pour 1 package of butterscotch pudding over frozen dough.

title: world famous meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in loaf pan.
Cover with tomato catsup.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven or until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix well with Cheddar cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Cook beef until browned; drain fat.
Add pepper and onions. Cook until tender.
Stir in everything else except cheese.
Spoon half of the meat mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with half of the cheese.
Spoon remaining meat mixture over cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Let stand loosely covered until cheese melts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pasta salad
directions: Pour dressing over combined noodles and vegetables.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator several hours.
Drain.
Combine salad dressing and cheese; mix well.
Add to vegetable mixture; mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: andrew's favorite chicken quiche
directions: Put chicken in unbaked crust.
Add cheese and mushrooms. Combine eggs and soup; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Saute onions and garlic in liquid butter.
If using fresh mushrooms, also saute them. If using canned mushrooms, wait to add them later. After onions are cooked, add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, pepper and other seasonings.

title: pink salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat; add pineapple.
Make Dream Whip separately.
Add Jell-O (mixed with 2 cups of hot water and 1 cup of cold water) to pineapple-cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix well shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add sour milk. Sift flour, soda and salt and stir in.
Mix in pecans, cherries, dates and vanilla.
Chill.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop with teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.
Good keepers and good travelers.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Mix half of cake mix with the egg, shortening and margarine. Mix well and then add second half of cake mix.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut out with round cookie cutter or top of a 1/2 quart or quart canning bottle.
Prick with fork (like you see on store bought sandwiches).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 minutes.
Fill with any flavor of ice cream and freeze in sandwich bags.
Makes approximately 12 to 18.

title: pork broccoli delight
directions: Prepare cooked pork.
Measure and set aside.
Put broccoli into boiling salt water for 2 minutes.
Drain.
Sprinkle croutons in bottom of shallow buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish. Top with broccoli.
Mix pork with mayonnaise and sour cream. Spread over broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate gravy(over 65 years old)
directions: Get milk scalding hot in a pan.
Mix all the rest of ingredients together and slowly add it to the hot milk, stirring all the time until it's thick enough for sopping with biscuit.

title: steamed fish
directions: Steam fish for about 10 to 15 minutes or until flesh is flaky. Heat soy sauce on medium.
Heat until boiling.
Add chopped green onions and remove from heat immediately.
(Onions will sizzle.) Place fish on a platter and pour soy sauce mixture over fish. Serve over rice with choice of vegetable.

title: southwest white chili
directions: Cook chicken in oil and remove from pan.
To pan, add chopped onion and cook for 2 minutes.
Add broth and spices and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in chicken and beans.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese.

title: taco shells (tortilla)
directions: Heat 8-inch skillet over medium-low heat just until hot.
Beat ingredients until smooth.
Pour scant 1/4 cup of the batter into skillet.
Rotate skillet until batter forms very thin tortilla, about 6-inches in diameter.
Cook tortilla until dry around the edges.
Fry in hot oil until crisp and golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake in ungreased loaf pan in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper in skillet, slowly at first; add salt, pepper, cominos, tomato puree and 1/2 can of water.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cook noodles or rice separately until tender and add to meat to cook, easy, for 30 minutes.
May be served like this or put in casserole and covered with grated cheese, browning in oven.
If you like very spicy food, add 2 packages McCormick Italian spaghetti sauce.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add lemon juice; bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil to jam stage, about 13 minutes.
When jam stage is reached, remove from heat. Stir and skim 5 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars; cool and seal.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: nacho dip
directions: In a casserole dish spread cream cheese 1/2 inch thick over bottom of dish.
Then pour chili over cream cheese leaving enough room to put as much Monterey Jack cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes for cheese to melt.
Use with your favorite nacho chips.

title: creamy broccoli cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, bring water to boil.
Add broccoli, return to boil.
Reduce flame.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Turn off flame.
Do not drain.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in milk gradually.
Add undrained broccoli and pepper. Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese spread; simmer 10 minutes.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: yogurt dressing
directions: In a small bowl, blend all ingredients.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken salad
directions: Drain chicken and pineapple.
Flake chicken apart and add the pineapple.
Add diced apple and the raisins.
Mix together and add mayonnaise as needed.

title: homemade summer sausage
directions: Mix well with hands; refrigerate 24 hours. Repeat mixing, then divide into 4 rolls. Cook 12 hours at 150°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jellos and hot water.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together other ingredients.
Add to jello.
Cool; enjoy!

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Cool, then slice thinly. Cook bacon until crisp then crumble. Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Heat in microwave until lukewarm just before serving.

title: southern raised biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and water.
Let set 5 minutes.
Then add buttermilk.
Combine dry ingredients and shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk and mix well. Turn onto floured surface and knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: frijole bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except Monterey Jack cheese and put in casserole dish.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread dumplings
directions: Stir all ingredients until moist.
Drop by tablespoon into greens with generous liquid.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes. Never remove cover while cooking.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: In a double boiler, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt; Stir in milk and beaten egg yolks; mix well.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and set aside.
In a quart size casserole dish, start layering with vanilla wafers in the bottom.
Next, add sliced bananas. Pour a portion of the custard over bananas.
Repeat layering, ending with custard on top.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until mixture forms a peak. Pile on top of pudding.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: fried hot water cornbread
directions: In a bowl, mix meal, butter and salt.
Instantly pour boiling water over meal.
Beat fast and hard.
Have a bowl of cold water to dip hands in.
Put about 1 to 2 tablespoons of mix in palm of hand and form flat pones or round pones.
Either fry immediately or place on waxed paper until all pones are formed.
Work fast. In a skillet, heat 1 1/2-inches cooking oil until hot. Drop pones in and fry until brown. Do not fry too fast, for the inside will not be done.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix and pour over carrots.

title: chop suey(china)
directions: Brown meat in a small amount of oil.
Transfer to a large saucepan.
Fry celery; add a small amount of water and steam for 10 minutes.
Add celery to meat.
Fry green pepper and onion together.
Combine meat and vegetables.
Add cup of water.
Mix cornstarch, brown sugar and soy sauce together.
Add to meat and vegetables.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add mushrooms 10 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.
May be made a day ahead.
Yields 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan and spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour mixture over melted butter. Drop peach halves on batter in pan. Pour juice of peaches on top. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: sesame baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water. Combine bouillon with seasonings; mix well.
Rub into chicken. Place skinned side down in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting with accumulated liquid.
Increase heat to 400°. Turn chicken and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake 10 minutes more for crispness.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter Bundt pan well or spray with oil. Boil water and add lemon jello.
Set aside to cool.
Add eggs one at a time to cake mix.
Add oil.
Add lemon extract and then cooled jello.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 40 minutes; test with toothpick.
Ice while hot.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In large bowl, combine and blend sugar and cocoa. Add milk and margarine (do not stir). Cook in microwave on High 2 minutes. Remove from microwave; stir. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir until blended. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill 1 hour.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Place zucchini in blender for 1 minute.
In large bowl, mix all other ingredients; mix well.
Now add zucchini to that mix and pour in pan.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until coconut is brown.

title: duck in mushroom sauce(serves 6.  preparation time: 3 hours.)
directions: Combine soup, red wine and chopped onion in a roasting pan. Wash duck and stuff with carrots and celery.
Place duck in roasting pan and cover with sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil and roast in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Garnish with parsley and serve over rice.

title: zesty butter sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Then cut each piece lengthwise to make 3 wedges (total of 6 wedges).
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Spread butter on cut surfaces of bread wedges.
Bake on ungreased 15 x 10-inch baking sheet near center of 425° oven for 7 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield: 6 (10-inch) sticks.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mash squash with fork.
Combine onion and butter mixture with slightly beaten eggs.
Add soup, squash, corn bread, salt and pepper and mix well.
Pour in greased casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Cut cheese into chunks and melt with meat. Blend in sour cream.
Serve warm with Tostitos.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs, flour, butter and extract. Add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and finish baking until brown.

title: oreo cookies
directions: Mix together.
Make into balls (1 teaspoon).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: salad elegance
directions: Layer all ingredients as described.
(A large salad bowl will be needed.)
Sprinkle 1/2 envelope Good Seasons (garlic flavored) over all.
Spread mayonnaise over all to completely cover and seal all edges.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Seal with plastic wrap or foil.
Keep in refrigerator until time to serve.
Toss and serve.
Will keep in refrigerator several days, if untossed and scooped into spoonful servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method.
Add milk, sugar, salt, egg, shortening and half of the flour to yeast.
Mix with spoon until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to handle easily.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth (5 minutes).
Round up in greased bowl; bring greased side up.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise in a warm place until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.
Let rise again until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.
Let rise again until almost double:
about 30 minutes.
Shape and let rise and bake as directed in recipes.
Roll dough into oblong 15 x 9-inch. Spread with 2 tablespoons softened butter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll up tightly, beginning at wide side.
Seal well by pinching edges together.
Even up roll by stretching slightly.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan or greased muffin cups.
Cover and let rise until double, 35 to 40 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost while warm with quick white icing.
Sift a little confectioners sugar into a bowl.
Moisten with milk to spreading consistency.
Add flavoring.
Spread over slightly warm bread.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oleo and 2 eggs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Mix well and spread over top of the first mixture.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Put tomatoes with juice, tomato paste, parsley, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and saute 2 minutes.
Add tomato mixture and wine.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 cups.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix crushed pineapple (well drained), thawed Cool Whip, coconut, miniature marshmallows, cherries and milk.
Chill for one hour.
It makes six servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange french toast
directions: Combine beaten eggs and orange juice.
Quickly dip bread into egg mixture, then into crumbs.
Fry on both sides in butter until brown.
Serve with butter and warm maple syrup.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and pat dry.
Tear spinach and lettuce into bite size pieces; toss with onion.
Combine olive oil, lemon juice and honey in a tightly covered container.
Shake well.
Just before serving, toss dressing with salad.
Sprinkle sesame seeds atop. Serves 6.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken (approximately 35 minutes) until cooked.
Use broth to cook spaghetti noodles.
Prepare noodles as directed on package but use broth instead of water.
Debone chicken.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper.
Saute until onions are clear.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted, then add cooked noodles.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut chicken into bite sizes.
Saute celery, peppers and onions in olive oil.
Add mushrooms, cheese, soups, broth, pimentos, olives and chicken.
Cook spaghetti noodles and mix with other ingredients.
Heat as a casserole at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 16.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: grandmother's belgium waffles
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm cream and milk in bowl.
Add flour, salt and sugar and mix.
Slowly add butter, stirring continuously. Fold in beaten egg white.
Make waffles thinnish, but cover all corners.
The best waffles ever!

title: sock-it-to-me-cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients and 1/4 cup water in mixer bowl.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour half the batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle mixture of pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon over batter.
Spoon in remaining batter.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool in pan for 25 minutes. Invert onto cake plate.
Drizzle with mixture of confectioners sugar and milk.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir until dissolved.
Squeeze water from broccoli and add to cheese mixture.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Beat 3 eggs and fold into mixture.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine.
Crumble crushed corn flakes over top.
Drizzle melted butter all over.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: italian omelet for saturday morning
directions: Add olive oil to an 8 inch skillet.
Add onions and bell pepper after olive oil is hot.
Add salt, black pepper, Emeril's Essence seasoning, and Italian seasoning.
Cook until onions are clear.

title: jam cake
directions: Separate the eggs.
Cream the butter and the sugar; add the jam and blend.
Add egg yolks one at a time and mix until smooth. Add flour and milk, alternately and blend after each addition. Add spices, nuts and raisins.
Fold in egg whites that have been well beaten.
Bake in a 250° oven until done.

title: enchiladas el paso
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, onion and seasonings.
Let simmer.
Dip each tortilla in hot oil.
Place tablespoonful of meat sauce and cheese on each tortilla; roll up tightly.
Place, seam side down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining meat and cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Saute and drain sausage; crumble over bread.
Beat eggs, mix in milk and salt. Pour egg mixture over bread and sausage.
Sprinkle cheese on top and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400°, covered, for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: easy quiche
directions: Prepare meat.
Place in pan and sprinkle with onions; layer with broccoli.
Cover with grated cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and Bisquick, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over all. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan for medium quiche.
Use 8 x 10 x 10 1/2-inch pan for deeper quiche.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Mix crushed wafers and melted oleo and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix with soup, egg, cheese and mayonnaise.
Season to taste.
Put in an 8-inch square Pyrex dish.
Combine melted butter and cornflakes; sprinkle over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Can be multiplied successfully.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: wine baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts, bone side down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange mushrooms around chicken.
Pour wine over chicken and sprinkle with parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple bread stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well, add pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes. Bake in a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole, uncovered for
50 - 60 minutes at 350 degrees until lightly browned.

title: munching peanut brittle(makes 1 pound)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and corn syrup; stir together.
Microwave at High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; microwave at High 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to mixture, blending well.
Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; stir until light and fluffy.
Quickly pour mixture onto lightly greased (use butter or margarine) cookie sheet or unbuttered nonstick coated cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix with all ingredients and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: stuffing meat loaf dinner(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Mix dry stuffing mix and seasoning packet with eggs and lean ground beef.
Place in crock-pot.
Turn heat to low setting, and cook for 6-8 hours.
Add catsup to top of meat loaf and potatoes around edges.
Cook for an additional 1-2 hours.
(If you prefer the traditional way of making the meat loaf this way, bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Omit the potatoes.)
This makes a great meat loaf and is very simple.

title: fresh berry pie
directions: Clean berries and place in the two baked shells.
Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Set off heat and add jello. Mix well and pour over berries in crust, being careful not to fill too full. Chill until set. Serve with whipped topping.
May use same flavor jello as berries.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: In a saucepan combine water and oatmeal.
Cook 1 minute.
Let stand.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Stir.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with butter frosting.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Place a large piece of foil on table.
Put pork chop in center of foil; sprinkle with salt.
Slice potato, carrot and onion and place around pork chop.
Add three tablespoons of water.
Foil foil up and seal edges.
Place on baking sheet and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: taffy sauce
directions: Mix in heavy pan until boiling.
Continue stirring for 15 minutes.
Take off heat and serve with apple slices.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Beat and pour eggs and milk over noodles.
Put in a 4-quart baking dish; sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Great for a crowd!)

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each.
Crush vanilla wafers.
Add, alternating with milk.
Add coconut and chopped pecans.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: breakfast treat
directions: Put cereal in bowl.
Add sliced banana, milk and sugar.
Stir up until sugar is mixed in real good.
Eat real soon or cereal with get soft.
Can also be made and eaten anytime of day or night as needed.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs and flour alternately.
Roll as thin as desired.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: tom thumb chewies
directions: Cut into small squares and serve.

title: bob's chili sauce
directions: Chop peppers and onions in food chopper or food processor. Mix remaining ingredients and add chopped vegetables in a large kettle.
Cook until thickened, 5 to 6 hours.
Pour into canning jars (7 to 9 pints).

title: peanut soup
directions: Grind the peanuts in a blender.
With a little oil, saute the peanuts in a skillet, but not until brown.
Put the peanuts, broth, onion, potatoes and carrots in a large pot.
Boil for 30 minutes. Add rice and peas and cook for 15 minutes more.
Serve hot with crushed parsley and French fried potatoes on top.
Serves 8.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 375°.

title: harry's salsa
