directions: Combine the ingredients in a large bowl and adjust consistency to suit yourself.
If you like your salsa on the saucy side, put the chunky bits in the blender and start experimenting.
Proceed with a light touch on the button.
If you like it chunky, and it's a little thin (because you didn't drain the tomatoes enough), now is the time to add a small amount of tomato sauce to thicken it up.
Be sure to experiment with this recipe until it suits your taste.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Whip cream until thick.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold cream and cheese mixtures together.

title: walnut chicken morsels
directions: In a bowl, blend the egg whites, cornstarch, garlic and salt until the mixture is combined well.
Add the chicken pieces and toss them well with the mixture.

title: parsley rice
directions: Combine rice, salt, bouillon and water; cook according to directions.
Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add almonds and parsley.
Fold into rice.

title: berry delight
directions: Mix
graham
crackers,	1/4 cup of sugar and butter and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: yogurt cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle in water 1 teaspoon at a time.
Stir until dough forms.
Press about 3 tablespoons of dough in bottom and up sides of ungreased 6-ounce custard cups to within 1/2 inch of top. Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Carefully remove from cups with a small metal spatula; let cool completely on wire rack. Fill each cup with 1/4 cup of yogurt.
Makes 4 cups.

title: pie dough for cobbler
directions: Melt oleo or butter in pan and pour milk, sugar and flour, mixed well.
Add 2 cans fruit.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixer bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and bananas.
Bake in 3 greased, floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Double for two squash.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Melt the margarine in a large pot over medium heat. Saute celery, bell pepper, onion and carrots over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the broccoli and cabbage to the mixture.
Add the water and stir.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 15 to 25 minutes over medium heat, stirring frequently.

title: hot crab dip
directions: I always soften the cream cheese well.
The green onions and green pepper I chop in a food processor.

title: spiced pumpkin butter
directions: In pan, whisk all ingredients until combined.
Bring to a simmer; reduce heat to low.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes (until thick enough to hold shape on spoon).
As mixture thickens, stir more frequently to prevent scorching.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked prepared pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until desired thickness.

title: texas hash
directions: A pan in which the bird fits rather snugly but is not crowded is preferred.
After cleaning the cavity and inserting an onion or two (if stuffing is not desired), rub the outside of the turkey with salt and pepper and a little butter.
Place in pan.
A generous size piece of brown paper, brushed on both sides with bacon fat, margarine or shortening is then humped a bit and arched over the bird.
With a little persuasion, it can be curved as to cover the turkey without quite touching it.
Tie it securely in place around sides of pan.
Be sure it is tied tight.
Cut off any excess while you are greasing the paper; let the oven be heating to 500°.
Place turkey in oven.
When you hear a sizzling sound coming from oven, reduce heat to 400°.
Don't break the paper or let your curiosity or doubt tempt you to peek!
Don't even open the oven door.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with Jell-O; bring to boil.
Cool in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Fold whipped topping and buttermilk into pineapple mixture.
Cool in refrigerator for 2 hours.
You can use strawberry Jell-O instead of peach.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
When ready to serve, add 1 bottle (33.8 ounce) ginger ale.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Serve in small bowl for dessert.

title: honey chicken with crumb-topped tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut each chicken breast in half; remove skin and any fat.
Line 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with foil. Place chicken in dish.
In small bowl, mix mustard, honey, curry powder and lemon juice.
Brush mixture over chicken.
Bake chicken, uncovered, 40 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut out stem end of each tomato, then cut each tomato in half horizontally.
Place tomatoes, cut-side up, in 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Into small bowl, tear bread into small pieces; stir in Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over tomato halves.
Spray each tomato lightly with nonstick cooking spray.

title: sue's super sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread half of the olive oil over the bottoms of 2 baking sheets (with edges). Rub the rest of the olive oil over the outside of the tomatoes.
Place tomatoes, garlic and 1/2 of the basil on the baking sheets. Sprinkle with the salt and pepper.
Roast until the tomatoes begin to break down, and the skins start to peel off (1 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: crab cakes
directions: Saute onions and peppers in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add to crab meat.
Soak bread in milk until soft; add egg, bread, onions and pepper to crab meat.
Mix.
Shape into cakes and roll in bread crumbs; fry in oil until brown.

title: creamed zucchini soup
directions: In a 2-quart casserole combine zucchini, water, onion, bouillon cubes, pepper, garlic powder, dill weed and nutmeg.
Microwave for 8 minutes on High.
Puree in blender.
Pour back in bowl.

title: baked flounder
directions: Gash flounder on top and lay in a greased baking pan.
Cut potatoes in round slices and lay around fish.
Salt both fish and potatoes; slice onion and put over potatoes.
Cut bacon strips in half and lay over fish, potatoes and onions.
Pour oil and water over potatoes.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 400°.

title: gramp's farm banana bread
directions: Put bananas through potato ricer.
Add sugar, melted margarine and beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda two or three times and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in greased glass loaf dish one hour in 350° oven.

title: orange delight congealed salad
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O and marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Set this mixture aside to thicken. Cream the cream cheese and sugar, then add whipping cream.
Whip until mixture is smooth and thick.
Add thickened Jell-O, pineapple (drained) and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill for 4 hours.

title: make a meal - make a quesadilla
directions: Use 2 to 4 tablespoons of ingredients per person.
Slice vegetables.
Saute vegeburger with onion and garlic.
Put 1 tortilla in a large frypan on medium heat.
Add fillings of choice and put second tortilla on top.
Turn when bottom tortilla is starting to brown.
Serve with refried beans, corn and rice.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Blend flour, shortening and salt.
Cut in shortening until pieces are the size of small peas.
Beat egg; mix with water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture and toss lightly with fork.
Roll out onto floured board or wax paper.
Makes 3 single crusts.

title: risotto
directions: Saute onion and celery until translucent.
De-skin and fry sausage to a large pot.
Add rice, tomato paste, 2 cups of warmed chicken broth, add spices to taste and crushed garlic.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring periodically.
Continue adding warmed chicken broth as mixture absorbs liquid (about 2 cups at a time).
Be sure to stir periodically to prevent burning.
Enjoy with Parmesan or Romano cheese.

title: basic fondant recipe
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and blend.
Fondant should be consistency of cookie dough.
If too wet, add more powdered sugar.
If too dry, add more cream.
Keep refrigerated in an airtight container and fondant will store for several months. Add 2 to 3 drops of desired candy oil flavorings to each 1/2 cup of prepared basic fondant.

title: pizza rice casserole
directions: In large skillet brown the ground beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, sugar, pepper, oregano, parsley flakes.
Cover and simmer for 15 min.
Cook rice and combine with cottage cheese, 1/4 t. oregano, and 1/2 t. Italian seasoning.
Put 1/2 of rice mixture in a buttered 2 qt. casserole.
Top with 1/2 of meat-tomato sauce. Alternate layers, ending with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/2 c. shredded cheese and parmesan cheese as desired.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 min.

title: quick casserole
directions: Combine
first
six ingredients and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Remove
from heat.
Spoon mixture into flour tortillas and roll.
Place in oblong casserole dish.
Pour enchilada sauce over rolls, sprinkle with onion and grated cheese.
Bake until sauce is bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: *(I put raisins in pan with a little water and cook until plump and tender.)

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix white or yellow cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over mixture and bake until cake tests done.
Let cool to lukewarm before turning out.
Bake at oven setting on cake mix box.

title: chuck roast
directions: Rub butter over roast; add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix onion mix with mushroom juice.
Spread mixture over roast and sprinkle mushrooms.
Roast for about 3 hours (pan covered with foil) at 350°.

title: sherry's spiced cherry sauce
directions: Drain cherries, reserving syrup.
Combine cherry syrup with remaining ingredients and dash of salt.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat. Stir in cherries.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute olive oil, onions, zucchini, green peppers, cubed potatoes, minced celery, diced carrots, crushed garlic and bean mix for 15 minutes.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes, then add tomato puree, water or stock, dry red wine, salt, pepper, basil, oregano, chopped parsley and chopped tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: russian tea with pineapple
directions: Mix and store in jar.
Use 3 tablespoons to a cup of hot water.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and drain.	Place in 2 or 3 quart casserole.	Continue
to layer as follows:	second layer of frozen onion
rings,
third layer of green beans and fourth layer	by adding
liquid
from the beans to the soup and mix. Pour over beans and top with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. (Chicken, turkey, beef, etc. may be substituted.
Also vegetables and soups can be varied.)

title: green stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes and throw away. Scoop out insides of tomatoes and save. Grind all together through a food grinder or processor the insides of tomatoes, green pepper, onion, eggs and bacon slices. Add salt and pepper and keep adding biscuits until you have the consistency of dressing. Place tomato hulls in large pan and stuff with the stuffing mixture. Add water until it is halfway on tomato shells. Bake (covered) in medium oven, 350°, for 30 to 40 minutes, then (uncover) and brown tops for approximately 5 minutes in oven.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat chili and cheese together until cheese melts.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: red punch
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: camp potatoes
directions: Slice bacon into 1-inch strips and fry in pan until crisp. Remove bacon; drain on paper towel.
Add potatoes and onions to bacon fat; fry until lightly browned.
Add bacon, salt and pepper. Cover and cook slowly for approximately 15 minutes.

title: almond bark pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Dip pretzels into bark, coating completely.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Makes 5 pints.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Place apples in pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Melt butter, add sugar and stir.
Add egg and mix well.
To this, add dash of salt and flour.
Mix ingredients well.
Spread mixture over apples in pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: sliced tomatoes with fresh basil
directions: Arrange the tomatoes neatly on a serving platter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add the chopped onions and basil.
Sprinkle with the oil and vinegar and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn stuffing balls(a crock-pot recipe)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine celery, onion, corn, water, pepper, thyme, stuffing mix and eggs.
Shape into 7 or 8 balls.
Place in slow cook pot.
Pour butter over balls.
Cover and cook for 3 to 4 hours on low heat.
Serve with broiled meats or roasts or use as extra dressing for chicken or turkey.

title: jiffy meat roll
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease baking sheet.
In large skillet, brown hamburger.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until onion is tender; drain any excess fat.
Blend baking mix and milk to soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and roll into rectangle, 9 x 12-inches.
Cover with meat mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk with mixer.
Then stir in all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: fast saucepan brownie
directions: In a pan, melt butter.
Take off and add sugar, cocoa, vanilla, eggs, flour, baking powder and pecans or walnuts.
Pour into square metal pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, not too done.
Cool.
If in glass pan, bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until barely done.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Wash rhubarb and cut in small pieces.
Cook with sugar until rhubarb is very tender.
Remove from heat, add pineapple and jello.
Mix thoroughly and cool.

title: molly's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 3 ingredients in paper bag. Put foil in bottom of cookie sheet.
Spray with nonstick spray. Shake 2 pieces in bag each time and place, skin side down, on sheet.
Melt butter in measuring cup and drizzle over chicken. Bake for 40 minutes, then turn and bake for 30 minutes.

title: perfect trio salad
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and add water to make 1/2 cup.
Heat to boiling.
Add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Add lemon juice, vinegar and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in drained pineapple, carrots and green pepper.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Unmold onto lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mrs. turner's crab casserole
directions: Make sauce with flour, butter and milk.
Saute butter with bell pepper and onion.
Add pepper and onion to sauce.
Mix mayo, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, crab meat and salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas, milk, flour and nuts.
Beat well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spray 9 x 13 baking dish with Pam. Add pie filling and pineapple. In separate bowl, mix melted butter and cake mix with a spoon (will be sticky). Pinch off and drop into dish. Add pecans. Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on baking pan and bake until done, around 12 to 15 minutes. Let cool completely. Mix cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise together. Spread onto baked crescent rolls. Pick around 4 vegetables (a small amount will do) and chop up fine and sprinkle on top. Mash vegetables down a little so they will stay on top of cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of mixture. Keep cool until ready to serve.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Combine Bisquick, red pepper, and 1/2 tsp. garlic powder.
With fork, stir in milk and cheese. Drop dough by 1/4 cup full onto a greased or lined cookie sheet. Combine melted butter and 1/4 tsp. garlic powder, and brush on top of dough.
Bake 10-12 minutes or until golden.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: deluxe rice casserole
directions: Sauce: Combine onion and green pepper in margarine until done, but not brown. Add rest of ingredients. Mix all together. Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven. Top with grated cheese.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool and cut cake into 1-inch pieces. Blend pudding and milk.
Layer as follows in a clear bowl:
1/2 cake pieces, 1/2 pudding mixture, 1 tub Cool Whip, 1/2 crushed candy and repeat layers.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: aunt mary's cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan.
Top with 1 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle 1 stick melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: la fonda del sol(a hearty mexican dip!)
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion in large skillet; add ketchup and spices.
Mash beans with their liquid; add to meat mixture.
Place meat mixture in bottom of chafing dish or other serving dish that can be kept heated.
Top meat mixture with an outer ring of grated cheese, an inner ring of onions and a center of sliced olives. Keep hot and serve with chips.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Add alternately with flour and mix.
Add vanilla.
Pour in buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: bananas flambe
directions: Cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Toss in lemon juice.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and margarine in a large skillet.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until sugar melts.
Add bananas.
Stir gently and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat.
Pour brandy over banana mixture and ignite.
Let flames die down and serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Blend cream cheese, egg, chocolate chips, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt together.
Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, soda, oil, vanilla, 1/2 teaspoon salt, cocoa, water and vinegar.
Fill 2 paper-filled cupcake tins approximately 2/3 full with second mixture.
Put spoonful of first mixture on top; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 24 cupcakes.

title: reduced sodium herb baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Arrange carrots and onions in a shallow baking dish.
Place chicken, skin side up, over vegetables.
Pour 1/2 cup of the stock over chicken; cover tightly and bake 45 minutes.
Meanwhile in a small pan, bring to a boil remaining stock, lemon juice, rosemary, thyme, marjoram and pepper.
Remove from heat; increase oven temperature to 400°.
Uncover chicken and bake, basting with herb mix for 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and skin is browned.
Spoon vegetables over chicken and serve.
Makes 4 servings, 107 mg. sodium per serving.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions in 13 x 9 pan.
Cool.
In bowl, whisk milk and pudding.
Let stand to thicken.
Stir in pineapple and spread over cake.
In a bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add whipped topping. Spread over pudding.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. 12 to 15 servings.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add spices and mix.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Mix well.
Place on party rye bread.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in 9 x 9 pan. Make 3 holes: one for oil, one for vinegar and one for vanilla. Pour water over all. Mix until evenly blended. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brown sugar syrup
directions: Place sugar, salt and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes (the cover prevents crystals from forming around the edges of pan).
Remove from the heat and add vanilla.
Store in a covered glass jar in a cool place.
Makes 1 cup of syrup.

title: bean pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add onion, salt, peppers, tomato soup, water and pinto beans.
Blend together.
Make up a small amount of corn bread.
Pour beef mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread corn bread batter on top of beef mixture.
Bake at 350° until corn bread browns on top.

title: summer time pasta
directions: In saucepan melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour and cook 2 minutes until bubbly.
Remove from heat and whisk in milk. Return to heat.
Bring to a simmer and cook over medium heat until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese, basil, salt and pepper.
Set sauce aside.

title: golden delight pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend at high speed 1 minute, stopping to stir down once.
Bake on greased griddle, using 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake.
Makes 20 (4-inch) pancakes.
This also makes excellent waffles.
Waffles can be frozen.
Reheat in toaster.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together (well) then add margarine, flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Take out of oven and cover with marshmallow cream and frosting.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cut the chicken into serving-size pieces and place in a kettle with the celery.
Add just enough water to barely cover the meat, cook, covered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until a fork will pierce the thickest part of the breast.
Drain off and strain the broth and place it in the refrigerator so that the fat will solidify and can be skimmed off.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice for 8 minutes; rinse well.
Add 3 chicken flavored bouillon cubes to fresh water and cook for 8 to 10 minutes more. Drain and let cool.
Mix all ingredients together, adding S & W white wine and herb vinegar lo-cal dressing to taste.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add the rest of the ingredients in pan.
Set pan in warm water and bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until set. Test center with a knife (dot with butter before baking).

title: my mexican style chili
directions: Brown beef with onion in large saucepan; drain.
Sprinkle chili powder and cumin over meat (may use packaged chili mix). Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ladle into bowls.
Serve with crackers or corn bread.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turkey cobb salad
directions: Prepare the first 7 ingredients.
Arrange decoratively in rows on a large platter.
Sprinkle with the parsley.
Present with vinaigrette and serving bowls along side.

title: custard pie
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients except cinnamon (taste mixture - you may need to add sugar).
Pour into unbaked pie shell. (If you have too much, bake extra in custard cups.)
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 420° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until set.
Do not overcook.
Serve with Cool Whip, warm or cold.

title: one pan stroganoff
directions: In a large frypan, cook the beef, onion and garlic until the meat is browned; drain off any fat.
Drain the mushrooms and reserve the liquid.
Add this liquid, beef broth and lemon juice to the skillet.
Stir in the uncooked noodles.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes until the noodles are tender.
Add more liquid if necessary.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Lightly grease and flour a 9-inch pie pan. In a large bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add 1 cup sugar and cream of tartar. Continue beating until whites form very stiff peaks. Gently fold in cracker crumbs, coconut and pecans. Spread mixture onto the bottom and up the sides of pie pan. Bake for at least 1 hour, until it looks very dry and surface starts to crack. It will be very light brown; will not brown like a meringue baked at a higher temperature. Cool completely and then refrigerate.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Serve hot with taco chips.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; place on oven rack.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour. Remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 400°.
Split potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out potato from shell; mash with cream cheese, milk, butter and salt.
Re-fill potato shells and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Place on baking sheet and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken with noodles
directions: Boil chicken, cool and debone.
Cook noodles in 3 cups chicken stock according to package directions.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in oleo.
Add sliced olives, mushrooms and chicken.
Mix well.
Drain noodles and
add
soup.
Add Velveeta to the vegetables and let cheese melt,
Mix everything together and moisten with stock if needed.
Place in a casserole dish, top with buttered bread crumbs or cornflake crumbs and heat at 325° until hot.
This can be frozen.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Fry in pan with oil, like a crepe.
Pour a small amount onto hot oil.
Fry 1 side, flip and fry the other side, less than 1 minute.
Add drop of oil every 3 or 4 crepes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Melt margarine and mix it with the stuffing mix.
Make sure all stuffing mix is well moistened. Put half of this mixture in the bottom of a casserole dish and put the chicken on top.
Combine sour cream, soup, broth, salt and pepper; pour on top of chicken.
Put remaining stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: lemonade party cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9 pan. Let cake cool for 15 minutes. Poke holes in cake with large fork about every 1/2-inch.

title: frosted walnut meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes and pack into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Let stand in pan about 5 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Turn meat loaf onto ovenproof platter.
Cover top and sides with creamy whipped potatoes.
Return to oven and bake about 10 minutes until potatoes are lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain wax, green and kidney beans.
Add all other ingredients. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Stir several times with a slotted spoon.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter and sugar until soft and creamy.
Add vanilla. Stir in pecans and flour.
Form dough into walnut-sized balls. Bake on well-greased cookie sheet at 300° for 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot and again when cold.

title: crisp pastel cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly the sugar, Jell-O, eggs, vanilla and shortening.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot dip
directions: Saute pecans and salt in margarine.
Cream the cheese and all other ingredients.
Spread cheese mixture on pie plate and top with pecans.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: sweet zucchini relish
directions: Put vegetables through food grinder.
Mix with the salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse with cup of water and drain well in colander.

title: bouja(new smaller version)
directions: First Day:
Early morning, put beef and oxtail in a large crock pot covered with water.
Put chicken in a second large crock pot covered with water.
Cook all day, covered.
In the evening, remove beef and all bones from broth to bowl.
Allow to cool until it can be handled.
Pull all meat off bones and return meat to broth.
Do the same with chicken, remove from broth, debone and return meat to broth.
Put both in refrigerator overnight.

title: basic broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion; drain.
Mix other ingredients together in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
This is a holiday standard dish in our home!

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Beat together oleo, sugars, peanut butter, soda, salt, vanilla and egg. Stir in flour and oatmeal. Spread dough in bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips on the top and return to the oven long enough to melt the chips. Spread chocolate evenly. Cool slightly.

title: e-z corn dogs
directions: You will need corn dog sticks.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Fry pork until crisp.
Add onions and cook until brown.
Add potatoes, celery, water and bouillon cubes.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in milk, butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Add chicken; heat until hot.
When ready to serve, stir in chopped eggs.
Reheating improves flavor.
(Can add a little thickening.)

title: janet's bread
directions: Mix
first 5 ingredients well.	Add a little flour at a time, mixing well, until dough leaves the sides of bowl.	Put flour
on table.
Knead
dough until smooth and elastic.
Put back in bowl and cover with towel.
Let rise until doublefold. Grease loaf pans.
Shape dough into 4 or 5 loaves and place in pans.
Grease tops of loaves with melted butter or margarine. Cover with towel and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes
to
1 hour.
Butter tops of loaves when you remove them from the oven.

title: creamed chicken on biscuits
directions: Measure broth and soup in saucepan.
Blend well and heat. Combine flour and water until smooth; stir into soup mixture until thickened.
Add chicken and simmer until heated.
Make biscuits from Bisquick recipe on box.
Serves 4.

title: yogurt-gelatin
directions: Prepare gelatin according to directions and chill until it starts to set.
Add yogurt and stir until well mixed.
Pour in a mold and chill until set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add salt and sugar and beat.
Beat in oil.
Mix flour, cinnamon, soda and baking powder and add alternately with grated zucchini.
Add nuts, coconut and raisins and mix well. Turn into three well-greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 55 minutes on lowest rack.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In soup pot, brown onion and butter, then add water and bouillon cubes and bring to boil. Add broccoli and boil for 5 minutes. Then add noodles and boil for 5 minutes. Add milk and cheese (cut in pieces). Warm until cheese melts.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix sugar with softened butter and milk to make a batter. Roll out flat to about 1/8-inch thickness (more or less).
Add milk and/or sugar to make it easy to work with.
Wrap each cherry with a circle of "dough."
Place on cookie sheet covered with waxed paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate pieces with shortening.
Dip each cherry into hot chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until firm and enjoy!

title: karo pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix sugar and flour and combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook in oven at 350° until firm or until knife comes out clean, approximately 45 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Crush corn flakes and mix with other ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish and bake until cheese is melted and casserole is heated thoroughly.
Top with grated cheese.
Serves 6.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Drain crab meat and pour lemon juice on meat.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to crab meat and lemon juice.
Put in saucepan and heat at low temperature.
Place in serving bowl or chafing dish and serve with assorted crackers, chips or cubes of French bread.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream oil and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Beat well until smooth.
Fold in egg whites. Pour in 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Put diced eggs in pan; add drained tuna and mushrooms.
Add cheese to White Sauce.
Cook until melted, then mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, cream of mushroom soup, salad dressing and eggs.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: judy's brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix by box directions.
Place half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: quiche
directions: Put layer of meat, onions and mushrooms in bottom of pie shells.
Add Swiss and cheddar cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together in a bowl.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: peanut butter dippers
directions: Using a cutting board, break the chocolate square into pieces with a paring knife.

title: country apple cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk, eggs and apples and blend well.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar in bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture clings together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine eggs, lemon juice, sugar, salt, baking powder and 1/4 cup flour in bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake for 25 minutes longer.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly. Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough by teaspoonful and roll into balls.
Roll the balls in a mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: crunchy spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Cover and chill overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers or assorted raw vegetables.
Makes 4 cups.

title: jelly rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put dough on board and knead until stiff enough to roll out. Roll dough out, then put butter and jelly on the dough. Roll it up and put in a baking dish.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together coconut and nuts; put in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour over coconut and pecan mixture.
Place butter and cream cheese in a saucepan and heat until mixture is warm enough to stir in powdered sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon this mixture over the top of the unbaked cake mix.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Do not cut until cool.

title: cheesecake ice cream with blueberry syrup
directions: Chill a medium mixing bowl and the beaters of an electric mixer in the refrigerator. Prepare an ice cream maker according to the manufacturers instructions.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Add fruit and mix well; let stand for 20 minutes.
Spoon into 9-inch pastry shell. Don't use butter.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lime and lemon ice cream
directions: In a very large mixing bowl, combine milk, sugar, whipping cream, lemon juice, lime juice and lemon extract; stir to dissolve sugar.
(The mixture may appear slightly curdled.)
Freeze in a 5-quart ice cream freezer and ripen ice cream according to the manufacturer's directions.
If desired, garnish with lemon and lime slices.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until almost tender; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: freezer tomato sauce
directions: Cut tomatoes into chunks.
Mix all ingredients in large kettle.
Bring slowly to boiling, stirring often.
Lower heat; simmer 30 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Cool slightly, then measure 3 cups at a time into blender.
Cover and blend until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into Ziploc freezer bags.
Makes 16 cups.
Freeze.
Good for soups and chili.

title: pink dessert
directions: Put pineapple with juice, sugar, water and dry Jello in pan. Bring to a good boil.
Cool.
When partially set, add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: gold coast pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops; pour off the fat.
Stir in soup, 1/2 cup water, carrots and onions.
Cover and let simmer 15 minutes.
Add peppers and let cook 15 minutes.
If you have an electric skillet, use it; if not, use an iron one.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: candied hot peppers
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pick peppers up in hands and add to mixture. Cook for 5 or 10 minutes.
Spoon peppers into hot jars.
Add liquid to cover peppers and seal.
Good on sandwiches, hamburgers, etc.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Add corn. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggs in spanish sauce
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash; stir in mayonnaise, mustard and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Stuff egg whites with yolk mixture.
Arrange egg halves in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Stir in flour, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and dash of pepper.
Add undrained tomatoes and bay leaf.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove bay leaf and pour over eggs.
Toss together crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle atop.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together like pie dough press into pan (9 x 13-inch). Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: angel hair salad
directions: Cook angel hair pasta according to directions. While pasta is cooking, cut up the vegetables.
Mix pasta, vegetables, dressing and spices while pasta is still warm. Top with grated cheese. Refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, fruit cocktail, soda and eggs.
Pour in greased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage and egg breakfast pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent rolls into eight triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press crescent rolls together to form a crust and seal perforations.
Sprinkle cooked sausage evenly over crust. Top with potatoes and diced bell peppers.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Combine beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake the pizza for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is browned and eggs are set.
Makes 1 pizza.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: daddy's burritos
directions: Fix taco meat according to directions on package.
Once taco meat is cooked down, add beans and cook over low heat until mixture is hot.

title: aunt frances' orange pound cake
directions: Cream butter, crisco, and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Sift flour,
baking powder, and salt together.
Add dry mixture alternately with orange juice to creamed mixture.
Add grated orange peel.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Start in cold oven.
Turn to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately after taking out of oven.
Poke holes in top.

title: spicy autumn applesauce
directions: Bring water, lemon juice, sugar and salt to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add apples, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg; cook about 10 minutes until apples are almost tender.
Turn off heat, but leave on burner, cover and let stand for 10 minutes to plump and finish cooking.
Use a hand potato masher, food processor or food mill to sieve apples to desired consistency (I prefer hand masher).

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil sweet potatoes for about 1 hour until soft.
Drain; slip skins off and mash in large bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add butter, sugar, light cream, eggs and spices.
Pour into buttered 2 quart baking dish and bake until center of souffle is set, 30 to 40 minutes.
Raise oven temperature to 475°.
Place marshmallows on top to cover.
Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes to brown.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter and cocoa in a microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir in powdered sugar and milk.
Cook in a microwave for 30 seconds. Stir in the vanilla and pecans and cook in microwave 30 seconds. Stir in marshmallows until dissolved.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2 pan.
Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: melba cheesecake pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat. Add crumbs and sugar; press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes; remove pan from oven.
Arrange peaches on crust.
Heat cream cheese in saucepan until soft; add remaining ingredients except jam.
Return to oven.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pretzels
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat egg yolks until lemony.
Work with hands or a spoon, the butter and egg yolks into the flour.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roll out, slice and shape as desired.
Brush pretzels with milk and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake on a cookie sheet in preheated 350° oven for about 10 minutes, turning once.
Really good with melted Cheez Whiz over them.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, beat the eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean; set casserole in a pan with water to bake for a better consistency.

title: best ever doughnuts
directions: Pour milk in bowl.
Add sugar, Mazola, salt and nutmeg.
Add yeast last.
Add flour and knead with dough hooks until well blended.
Turn out on floured board and knead by hand only until you can handle it.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and allow to rise for 5 minutes.
Deep fry in Mazola at 375°.
Drain doughnuts on paper towel.
Frost doughnuts and dip in slivered almonds, chopped nuts or coconut.

title: grandma's chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine broth, noodles, onions, celery and carrots and bring to a boil over high heat, about 10 minutes. Reduce heat and simmer partially covered 10 minutes. Stir in chicken and parsley and cook until heated through, 5 minutes more. Makes 8 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Stir butter, flour and milk constantly until they come to a boil.
Add cheese gradually.
Pour over cooked macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (put in a lasagne pan).

title: hi ho meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then turn oven down to 325° and bake 1 more hour.

title: sumptuous salad
directions: Clean lettuce and drain.
Start with 2 cups of lettuce torn into bite size pieces.
Take 3 tablespoons of mayonnaise and dot over lettuce.
Scatter 1 portion of the peas over the lettuce. Scatter 1/2 cup Swiss cheese and 1/2 cup red onion over the lettuce.
Scatter 3 tablespoons of sugar over the lettuce.
Put 2 more cups of lettuce in and go through the same steps as before. Continue with third cups of lettuce, etc.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Cream.
Make paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add butter and salt with flour.
Add vanilla.
Fold in soda and vinegar.
Bake on medium speed about 2 minutes.
Bake in two 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Split layers, if desired and ice.

title: chickpeas dip
directions: Reserve the liquid from chickpeas.
Cover peas with water and boil 5 minutes.
Drain water.
Place garlic and lemon juice in blender.
Process until garlic is liquid.
Add tahini.
Blend until smooth.
Add chickpeas and blend until smooth.
Salt to taste.
Spoon onto platter.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour a 9-inch square pan.
Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
In separate bowl mix together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add egg mixture; stir well.
Mix in raisins and nuts. Pour into pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Spread with frosting.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch squares.
Refrigerate. Makes 27 bars.

title: dutch soup
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into large pot. Add 1 can water and boil mixture.
Mix hamburg, pork, bread, egg, salt, pepper and parsley and form into small meatballs.
When pot is boiling, add meatballs and gently fold them in.
Cook slowly about 4 hours; add salt and pepper if needed.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
Freezes well.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until well blended. Store in airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup mix to 2/3 cup hot water.

title: apricot-glazed ham patties
directions: Combine ham with next 9 ingredients.
Shape into 6 patties. Place in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Combine preserves, vinegar and mustard.
Brush on ham patties.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: s.o.s.
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger meat.
Do not drain.
Add flour (sufficient amount to make a gravy).
Add milk until just barely covers meat in pan.
If gets too thick, add more.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on white bread.

title: aunt abbie's bean soup
directions: Add enough water to mix all ingredients together.
In a crock-pot, cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork
chops on medium heat.
Place rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with pork chops.
Place onion slices on pork chops.
Pour consomme over all. Cover dish with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked oysters in shell
directions: Scrub oyster shells thoroughly.
Rinse under cold running water.
Open oysters using the method recommended by the Fishery Council.
Discard flat shell.
Keep deep halves for use.
Start oven at moderately hot (400°).
Melt butter, season with parsley and a quick grind of black pepper.
When butter is slightly cooled, roll each oyster in it barely coating oyster.
Return oyster to shell.
Squeeze lemon juice over oysters and cover each with crumbs.
Place filled shells in shallow baking pan.
Bake 5 minutes.
Add light sprinkling of salt to oysters and continue baking 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients in baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover with crackers and poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: micro meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into loaf and put in microwave-proof baking dish.
Cook on High 8 to 10 minutes, or 140° on microwave thermometer or probe.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry ground beef.
Layer beef, potatoes, onion and carrots. Top with soup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: bill and leah's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time; mix well. Add alternately flour and 7-Up or clear drink.
Add vanilla or lemon extract.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 325° oven.
